"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Farm for the Dominion."
"Tovisa wants help at Northwind Mine. The Reachmen have taken over the mine and we need to find out why."
"I received a contract from the Speaker."
"Gotta kill 'em all."
"The Spider Cult has come to Fungal Grotto. Members of the Fighters Guild
"Zone": are determined to stop the Cult from raising an army of shadows that will destabilize the region."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Mine for the Dominion."
"I met a Nord woman who's searching for her father in the northern hills of the Rift."
"I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Keep for the Pact."

"I met two Nord soldiers near the shrine of Kynesgrove. They claim that the shrine has been taken over by evil witches and that the rest of their brigade never returned from the shrine. Now they just wait
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "I've discovered evidence of something amiss at the Windridge Caves in Alcaire. The fates of a knight and his comrades seem inexorably tied to the existence of The Three
"InternalName": a trio of bandit chieftains who once dwelled in these caves."

"Zone": wants to slow down the bombardment of Imperial City from the Elven Gardens District."

"Journal": "I met a Dark Elf named Telbaril in a pocket of Evergloam known as Crow's Wood. He's trying to find his missing father
"InternalName": Rulantaril. He asked for my help."

"Journal": "Blessed by Veloth
"InternalName": I've come to Eidolon's Hollow to confront Magistrix Vox. It's time to end her threat once and for all."

"Journal": "I must inform Lord Vincintian of an assassin in Camlorn."
"I've come upon <<1>>
"InternalName": a sun-baked wanderer. He inhabits a murky oasis near Tu'whacca's Throne. The wanderer seems to be speaking in fables regarding Sep's Hunger and a pearl."

"Journal": "Countess Virolynn believes Gargast is bound for a town called Crosswych in Dwynnen.  Who ever he reports to
"InternalName": likely tied to this Shourded Thone

"Journal": "Dragons have not been seen in Tamriel for generations
"InternalName": and the Khajiit are unsure how best to fight against them. The ancient Nords recorded Dragon fighting techniques on scrolls they keep in their crypts. I need to find these scrolls."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Dortene wants the <<1>> captured and brought into Covenant hands."
"<<1>> wants to get rid of <<2>>
"InternalName": the Khajiit in Alten Corimont. Since the Khajiit is running Dominion supply lines
"Zone": her sudden demise would benefit both <<1>> and the rest of Shadowfen."

"Journal": "I decided to ask Faraniel for help getting into the tower. Before she shows me the secret
"Zone": she wants me to help her convince the Wood Elves to leave the forest and stop working for Molag Bal."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Castle Roebeck for the Dominion."
"While detouring through the swamp
"InternalName": the Bagot family was attacked by a powerful Bog Lurker. Their daughter Isabelle went missing in the chaos. Tristan
"ZoneID": limped to the caravan to find help

"Journal": "I shared everything I learned with Councilor Ralden. He plans to seal Narsis so that no one can enter or leave. I've been granted an exception while I work for the councilor."
"Jes of Wayrest told me a shipment of weapons he sent to Eagle's Watch was taken by who bandits who prey on travelers near Camlorn. Jes doesn't want his weapons in the hands of these villains."
"Sir Lanis and the Knights of the Dragon are ready to march into Cath Bedraud to deal with Angof
"InternalName": but the mist rising from Angof's vines creates a hazard they can't overcome."

"Journal": "Oron awaits word from High King Fahara'jad as how to proceed with King Sebastien.  While he waits he asked me to ask Sebastien about the Shrouded Throne."
"Katarin delivered Ranser's murder weapon to Countess Virolynn in Aldcroft manor."
"It appears a hunting band was overcome by a powerful wispmother
"InternalName": as their frozen forms are scattered about the mire."

"Journal": "I found a letter on a dead man in Bearclaw Mine."
"Commander Lafavre has asked you to find some of his soldiers who have not reported back. He is afraid they are in danger."
"The forest itself seems to have turned against the village of Deleyn's Mill and the villagers are in danger. I should see if I can help."
"Abelard Yves has asked me to look into the issue of spirits who are haunting the roads outside Camlorn and disrupting trade. Camlorn is a big city
"InternalName": but the townspeople should be able to point me in the right direction."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Mine for the Covenant."
"Cyrodilic Collections
"InternalName": a society dedicated to locating and restoring Argonian antiquities
"Zone": seeks help in its mission. They want to stay ahead of their competition and preserve every piece of Argonian culture they can."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Keep for the Covenant."
"To save the members of the Mages Guild that were forced to compete in the Observer's game
"InternalName": I decided to side with Thallik. Now I just need to find a way to win the game."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Rayles Lumbermill  for the Covenant."
"Vestrial asked you to cleanse the Crypt of all evil."
"I accepted a mission to scout Fort Aleswell for the Covenant."
"Raynor and Kireth Vanos were recently marooned on the Gold Coast. The captain they hired to sail them to Sentinel delivered them to Anvil instead
"InternalName": and now they lack the funds to finish their journey. They asked me to help them find work."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help re- capture Castle Bloodmayne for the Dominion."
"Margot Oscent has a son named Lucas who's missing
"InternalName": and she's worried he may have been taken by the slavers."

"Journal": "Sergeant Oorga is afraid she will die in her next battle and asked me to deliver an offering to Azura for her."
"Roche suggested I hurry to find the courier
"InternalName": as the Spriggans are exceptionally dangerous."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Lumbermill for the Dominion."
"Inside a broken tower
"InternalName": I found a wounded woman named Imwyn Frost-Tree. She told me of a powerful symbol of her faith

"Journal": "The spirit of Richard Dusant said I should take the Dresan Index to someone in the Mages Guild."
"Guard Rila wants me to slow down a group of agitated citizens to keep them from getting killed. She asked me to disrupt their meeting by using something they fear. I need rats."
"I met a strange man who dislikes bears."
"<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Glenumbra."
"Baron Winoc tells me that Camlorn is in an uneasy state of truce between his Hands of Northmoor and the Magis Order. He is unsure where public opinion lies
"InternalName": and is too high-profile to ask around himself. He's asked me to ask around for him."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Warden Lumbermill  for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Mine for the Covenant."
"Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Yasammidan and gather as many historic relics as I can find."
"Disheveled NPC asked me to find a magical tome and bring it back to him. He says when I find it
"InternalName": I should quickly deliver it to him - there's no telling the evils abound..."

"Journal": "I'm now a full member of the Veiled Heritance. I've been told of a grand hall where their leadership council meets. And they are meeting with the Veiled Queen herself!"
"I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Mine for the Pact."
"The Elder Scroll of Altadoon has been stolen by the enemy."
"To save the Mages Guild members that were forced to compete in the Observer's game
"InternalName": I decided to side with Kinlady Estre. Now I just need to find a way to win the game."

"Journal": "The Forlorn One asked me to use the decanter of holy water to rescue two people trapped by the fires."
"The lumberjacks are fine for now
"InternalName": but many of their tools were damaged."

"Journal": "Acolyte Eldri collected Dremora hearts for Healer Dalen. He can turn the hearts into healing potions and wanted them to help the troops at Eidolon's Hollow. Unfortunately
"InternalName": Dalen departed before Eldri could give him the hearts."

"Journal": "Captain Noris came to Vivec's Antlers to defend against an incursion by Alexandra Conele of the Covenant. Alexandra wants to retrieve an artifact known as the Coral Heart from Vivec's Antlers. The Pact is barely holding its ground."
"There appears to be more to the Bloody Eye then it seems. Their leader keeps speaking of the battle against the flesh and the spirit
"InternalName": as if two different sources of a fight. I must find out what their true purpose is in order to get their assistance."

"Journal": "Lord Drugo has requested that I travel to Camlorn to warn Lord Sebastien of a possible assassination in his court."
"I found the last wishes of someone named Handre. He was going to use a gem he stole from the bandits to buy Fadeel's freedom."
"<<1>> discovered that Reach magic has somehow corrupted the forest and silenced the elemental guardians."
"I accepted a mission to scout Dragonclaw Farm for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Lumbermill  for the Covenant."
"I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Clothier goods to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I have simply sampled a taste of the spirit world known as the Veil as it seems I would be set to return on a journey into the darkness. Before I enter this realm
"InternalName": I must find what I must do in order to succeed in my goals."

"Journal": "Supernal Dreamers attacked Azura's shrine at Weeping Giant
"Zone": and stole many relics. The young novice
column8: asked me to help her recover them and look for a captured warden."

"Journal": "Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training."
"I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Lumbermill  for the Dominion."
"Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the frosty ruin of Direfrost Keep
"InternalName": which lies flush against the mountains of Eastmarch."

"Journal": "The Llodos plague has been unleashed and it's spreading through the gorge. Despite this
"InternalName": some Hlaalu guards are searching for the Maulborn alchemist."

"Journal": "There's been a murder in Camlorn. Someone named Ranser was killed
"InternalName": and because a neutral party is hard to find

"Journal": "The renegade Ashlanders have broken through a storage tunnel beneath Iliath Temple
"InternalName": taking the monks and their defenders by surprise. If the attack can't be repelled
"Zone": the monastery is sure to fall."

"Journal": "Tarrant Circe
"Zone": is having a bad year. His crops are failing and he can't figure out why. He thinks he may be the victim of sabotage from a neighboring farmer."

"Journal": "I met an Argonian named Onuja at Othrenis. He asked me to aid Davon's Watch in their battle against the Daggerfall Covenant."
"The spirits of four legendary Redguards stand around the central shrine atop HoonDing's Watch. Each poses a challenging choice based on a difficult decision they once had to make."
"The Ashen Order have asked me to break the will of the undead skeletons infesting Silvermist Castle. Their camp is just inside the Silvermist Castle entrance
"InternalName": but they are unable to move further forward."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Ash Mine for the Dominion."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Dragonclaw Farm for the Dominion."
"I've agreed to deliver a letter for a mysterious Imperial named <<1>>."
"Find Quest NPC's midget.  Apparently he likes to go and play with a 'puppy' somewhere in the zone."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Keep for the Covenant."
"A wealthy patron of the Thieves Guild takes a peculiar pleasure in owning stolen goods. Her tastes are mercurial
"InternalName": but her payments are like Dwarven clockwork."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Fort Dragonclaw for the Dominion."
"The Celestial Thief appeared to me and asked for my help discovering why the atronachs that were summoned to destroy the Dark Anchors turned against the mages of Craglorn."
"Dr. Holcombe has asked me to find clues to the source of the werewolf attack on Northmoor. I should return to him once I have gathered enough information."
"I met a sad looking dog beside a path in the Alik'r Desert. She seems to want my help."
"I accepted a mission to scout Ash Farm for the Dominion."
"Glutton
"InternalName": the prized pig that belongs to the Daggerfall swineherd Wickton
"Zone": is missing. Wickton suspects pig thieves
"ZoneID": or at least one particular pig thief."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Sorcalin needs vounteers to capture the <<1>>."
"<<1>> deciphered her father's ledger. She asked for my help with what she uncovered."
"A wine merchant named <<1>> was robbed on the road to Ebonheart. Now he's deep in his cups
"InternalName": and he wants help getting his shipment back."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Enchanter glyphs to an interested organization."

"Journal": "Julian Kalere told me that Supernal Dreamers have stolen his Crystal of Power and shattered it into five shards. They plan to use the shards as foci for daedric summoning rituals."
"Caldrun has tasked me with destroying the abomination that is Gargast. I must track him down and rid the world of him"
"An Orcish animal handler named Arushna is desperate to get her hands on special durzog feed that can only be found in the Kennel."
"The town of Crestshade has been subjected to a blood-curse that turned the townsfolk feral. While some refugees were able to escape to the south
"InternalName": the mayor remained behind to aid any survivors."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Lumbermill for the Pact."
"Brennoc has asked me to speak to Inquisitor Roche about a troublesome villager."
"I accepted a mission to scout Fort Ash for the Dominion."
"I visited all the High Kinlords and Kinladies of Summerset
"InternalName": seeking their support for Queen Ayrenn's invasion of Tamriel. This approval was symbolized in the forms of Batons of Fidelity
"Zone": which I entrusted to Canonreeve Lefalto's safekeeping."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Ash Mine for the Covenant."
"Ufgra is worried about a tribe of Goblins that has moved into Timberscar Hollow."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Mine for the Dominion."
"Orona
"Zone": mentioned that killing the kwama and letting them rot is a waste. She'd much rather harvest their cuttle
"ZoneID": which apparently has a lot of profitable uses."

"Journal": "Cleric Sellan has armed me with a blessed chain with which to bind the evil in Silvermist Castle. He believes the source is a crypt in the graveyard."
"Within Fort Sphinxmoth I encountered one of the chapel guards. She believes more of her companions were still alive elsewhere in the complex."
"Aldmeri Dominion forces have captured Farwatch Tower. They're using the tower to signal their fleet at sea."
"Now that I've recruited at least one of the people Kaleen wanted
"InternalName": we can pull off her heist whenever I'm ready."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Glademist Farm for the Pact."
"Dark Elves have been disappearing along the road to Narsis
"InternalName": near the western mountains. An incursion of Orcs may be responsible. I offered a Dark Elf scout my assistance."

"Journal": "I've agreed to help Oron
"Zone": prove King Sebastien is innocent of Ranser's murder. I'm to work with High Priest Canning of the Order of Arkay to summon Ranser's spirit
"ZoneID": so Ranser's shade can name his killer."

"Journal": "According to Centurion Gavo's confession
"InternalName": the Stonefire cult plans to summon a Dark Anchor within Arenthia."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Mine for the Pact."
"I visited all the High Kinlords and Kinladies of Summerset
"InternalName": seeking their support for Queen Ayrenn's invasion of Tamriel. This approval was symbolized in the forms of Batons of Fidelity
"Zone": which I entrusted to Canonreeve Lefalto's safekeeping."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Mine for the Dominion."
"After murdering Duchess Lakana
"InternalName": Sir Hughes fled to Firebrand Keep. I've come to confront him and if necessary
"Zone": bring him to justice for his crimes."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Bloodmayne Mine for the Dominion."
"Queen Maraya has asked a personal favor. She's heard disturbing rumors about some of her father's enemies returning
"InternalName": so she's asked me to go to Sentinel in the Alik'r Desert and ensure that both the kingdom and her father are safe."

"Journal": "High Priest Canning is almost ready to complete the ceremony to summon Ranser's spirit. I must be ready for whatever comes next."
"I decided to ask Tzik'nith for help getting into the tower. Before she shows me the secret
"Zone": she wants me to help her against the Wood Elves."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Keep for the Covenant."
"I've found a scroll bearing marks from the Aldmeri Dominion. It details a series of unsolved murders in <<1>>."
"Knarstygg and Dro-Dara have decided it would be wise to go to Wayrest until the bandits clear out of the plantation. Knarstygg is concerned that Murk-Watcher might not want to leave."
"Using the codebook I discovered
"InternalName": Adusa has determined that Montclair's nephew
"ZoneID": is behind the assassination plot. She believes that if we eliminate Rohlbert
column8: we can end this part of the Montclair threat once and for all."

"Journal": "I found a body weighted with heavy rocks in the sea beneath Camlorn's docks. I've decided to investigate the murder."
"Outside the ancient ruins of Skyreach Pinnacle
"InternalName": I met a member of the Scaled Court. He told me that the Court accidentally released creatures from magical wards the Nedes set up long ago. He plans to reestablish the wards

"Journal": "Captain Blanche Geves sent me to look for the Third Squad soldiers who were scattered after a vicious undead attack. They are near the Redoubt and may be pinned down
"I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Keep for the Dominion."
"Inquisitor Blarae has seen Morholdt as well - he has attacked the Redoubt many times. Also
"InternalName": the failed ritual in Camlorn caused the number of undead attacking the Redoubt to greatly increase. They threaten to overrun the Redoubt and destroy Camlorn."

"Journal": "The Drake of Blades wants me to recover a book that the Daedra refuse to burn and whose contents must therefore be very important."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to scout Castle Bloodmayne for the Covenant."
"Thetis has finished mixing a remedy he believes will clean out the lake."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Farm for the Covenant."
"I found an exquisitely carved urn within Old Sord's Cave. It appears to belong to <<1>> of Windhelm."
"The Ashen Order (a.k.a. the Gravebinders) have asked me to help cull the horde of undead infesting Silvermist Castle. Their camp is just inside the Silvermist Castle entrance
"InternalName": but they are unable to move further forward."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Farm for the Dominion."
"Clanmother Kazirra told me to travel to the city of Rawl'kha
"InternalName": to bring word of the Mane's change of heart."

"Journal": "<<1>> wants to know what really happened to <<2>>'s dowry. She has a plan to uncover the truth of what happened during the guild's failed heist."
"The Bloodthorn cult is attempting to take control of the spirits of High Rock knights laid to rest at the Burial Mounds. They also seek to control the ancient kings buried there
"InternalName": and have stolen their regalia for some dark purpose."

"Journal": "<<1>> believes the spirit of a long-dead mage may know the secret to imprisoning Balreth again. An Argonian scout named <<2>> has already left for Othrenis."
"Vestrial has asked you to recover the missing pages of his research book."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Mine for the Covenant."
"I visited all the High Kinlords and Kinladies of Summerset
"InternalName": seeking their support for Queen Ayrenn's invasion of Tamriel. This approval was symbolized in the forms of Batons of Fidelity
"Zone": which I entrusted to Canonreeve Lefalto's safekeeping."

"Journal": "The city of Camlorn has fallen to Faolchu and his werewolf legion. The Lion Guard struggles to retake the city
"InternalName": but the odds are against them."

"Journal": "Tervur Sadri
"InternalName": the co-owner of the Darkshade mine
"Zone": wants me to help him find his partner
column8: and get rid of the thugs who've displaced his miners."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Lumbermill for the Pact."
"Vaermina's ultimate plan has been revealed. Her consort
"Zone": has seized High King Emeric's mind and trapped him in a nightmare. I must face the Night Terror and save the king."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Mine for the Dominion."
"Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe
"Zone": wants me to go to Bok-Xul and accomplish the task he set before me."

"Journal": "Dubdil Alar's apprentice has hired me to stop one of her former master's experiments. I'm also required to gather his research notes for further study."
"The Numinous are to report to Queen Ayrenn for a Royal Fete. Proceed to the Immaculate Tabernacle in the Turquoise district."
"I accepted a mission to scout Dragonclaw Mine for the Covenant."

"Commander Lafavre has asked you to kill the bosses controlling the Halls of the Damned.
- Nazgol the Undying
- General Ripfang
- Bone Colossus
- Orutu
- Anarose Direblood
- Therion Direblood"
"I accepted a mission to scout Rayles Mine for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to scout Black Boot Farm for the Covenant."
"I am competing in the Sorcerer Division of Thizzrini Arena. I must fight through the ranks in order to fight Malarel
"High Mage Dilborn has asked me to find him some Nightmare Dust. He says it drops from the spectres that roam the lowest depths of the keep."
"Riekrs have been raiding caravans throughout Wrothgar
"InternalName": plundering cargo and taking travelers prisoners. The Riekrs

"Journal": "The Duke told me that Gloria has a plan to learn more about Faolchu and how to defeat him. She wants me to capture a living werewolf for the ritual she needs to perform."
"Sample Escort"
"I discovered a Mages Guild expedition at the ruins of Ezduiin. A scholar named Telenger is in charge."
"I've found the body of a hunter in the wilds. Nearby was a notice he dropped detailing a bounty on senche-tiger fangs."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Lumbermill for the Dominion."
"<<1>> believes his mother's remains lie in <<2>>
"InternalName": away from the swamp waters. Her spirit is unable to return to the Hist."

"Journal": "My long pursuit of Baron Blackmoore ends here
"InternalName": in his own keep. His crimes will not go unpunished
"Zone": and his death will be a message to all. Time for me to hunt him down in his own home."

"Journal": "<<1>> asked me to leave supplies at a cache for messengers who're going for help."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Lumbermill for the Dominion."
"Kassandra betrayed us-she claimed the sap-speaker's staff and set out after the Remnant on her own. I need to reach her before she takes the Remnant for herself."
"A large Maulborn force used the sewers to sneak into Mournhold. I need to find them before they can complete their nefarious plan."
"While I pursue the Baron through his keep
"InternalName": I need to keep watch for evidence of his dark magic."

"Journal": "Shornhelm
"Zone": is a city divided. House Montclair has annexed part of the city. Darien Gautier suggested I go to Shornhelm and help Countess Tamrith and Baron Dorell deal with the situation."

"Journal": "The city of Evermore is in dire straits. King Eamond is dead and Reachmen are bearing down on the city from the north. Duke Renchant plans to hand the city over to Imperial control
"InternalName": but I have agreed to work with Queen Arzhela to stop him."

"Journal": "King Emeric believes Count Hosni has the Dream Shard stolen from Pariah Abbey. He wants me to ingratiate myself with the count in hopes of retrieving the shard."
"I accepted a mission to scout Rayles Lumbermill  for the Dominion."
"<<1>> of the Dragonstar Caravan Company asked for my assistance in fulfilling a contract for a mage in the Silaseli ruins."
"The threat of the Llodos plague has allowed paranoia to run rampant. Many people in Narsis claim that friends and family members have vanished in the night."
"<<1>> had a Bosmer wife named Breloth who died recently. He's asked me to help him get things to give her a befitting burial."
"I accepted a mission to help regain Fort Aleswell for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to scout Chalman Keep for the Dominion."
"The Vinedusk Rangers want me to help quash the remnants of the Blacksap Rebellion
"InternalName": the Wood Elf civil war that ended with the Dominion's formation."

"Journal": "The Keeper has an intriguing contract that he feels I am just right for."
"Captain Janeve
"InternalName": the shield of the Shornhelm Guard and Countess Tamrith's younger sister
"Zone": has established a camp for refugees displaced by the vampiric menace."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Lumbermill for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help reclaim Farragut Keep
"Zone": and Kingscrest Keep for the Pact."

"InternalName": a New Life Herald in Eastmarch
"Zone": spoke of <<2>>'s New Life Festival in Stormhaven."

"Journal": "I met a Bosmer named Ongalion at the Falinesti Autumn site. He's a tree-steward
"InternalName": helping to tend the site while the city is away."

"Journal": "Vaermina has taken control of King Emeric's dreams and Abbot Durak says we need Azura's guidance."
"<<1>> met me on the road into Wind Keep and asked me to help the countess. She's acting strangely and it's put the entire town on edge."
"Three Pact soldiers were kidnapped in the Lion's Den: Hilka
column8: is certain one of them is a traitor. He has tasked me with identifying the traitor and freeing the others."

"Journal": "The Elder Scroll of Ghartok is being held by the enemy."
"The lighthouse south of Koeglin Village was attacked
"InternalName": and its signal fires were extinguished. Until someone repairs it
"Zone": ship captains will have difficulty navigating the harbor."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Lumbermill for the Dominion."

"Zone": and <<3>> are missing and likely in trouble. Snorrvild has asked me to help find them."

"Journal": "<<1>> is worried about Cropsford's books being destroyed in a Goblin attack."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Chalman Keep for the Dominion."
"The Fighters Guild has sentenced <<1>> to death for the murder of <<2>>."
"The Quarantine Master in Davon's Watch wants me to discover the fate of Fort Arand
"InternalName": which was recently engulfed in a Blightstorm.\n\nHe says this will prove that I am immune to the Blight

"Journal": "I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Mine for the Dominion."
"Sorderion has charged me with apprehending Aldolin
"InternalName": a traitor to the Dominion who has been giving aid to the Ebonheart Pact."

"Journal": "I helped Abnur Tharn decode the Wrathstone tablet and determine the location of the hidden weapon. Now we need to travel to the Halls of Colossus and find it before his half-sister
"InternalName": Euraxia. Khamira has decided to go with us."

"Journal": "My investigations of the Bloodthorn Cult's activities have convinced Chief Tazgol that they threaten the Orcs on Betnikh."

"The Knights of the Flame are divided over whether to attack the redguard army at Alcaire Castle. Sir Croix and other knights would potentially destroy the Covenant. They need to be stopped. I've agreed to rally knights to Sir Edmund's cause."
"Sir Edmund and the knights who have rallied to our cause are prepared to attack. We must retake Firebrand Keep and put an end to the plan that would threaten the Daggerfall Covenant."
"Forces of the Daggerfall Covenant are occupying the volcanic sulfur pools east of Heimlyn Keep. The Othrys family worked the site
"InternalName": but they've been run off their property."

"Journal": "The Red Rook bandits have taken control of the town of Crosswych. Some of the townsfolk are trying to organize a resistance
"InternalName": but the bandits are determined to use the town as a base."

"Journal": "The Naga-Kur
column8: to death for interfering in the rites of passage and saving a few young Nagas from certain death. One of the survivors asked if I could help Kishi."

"Journal": "While searching for an exit to the Bone Vaults
"InternalName": I have uncovered a hidden library."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Warden Farm for the Covenant."
"I've helped track down the source of the poison in <<1>>
"InternalName": but the poisoner still remains to be found. I should work with <<2>> to bring the culprit to justice."

"Journal": "I seem to have found some Dwemer ruins.  I should explore and see what I can find."
"Duke Sebastien of Camlorn has been kidnapped by Bloodthorn cultists."
"I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Mine for the Dominion."

"The Missir-Dadalit Egg Mine has been overrun with kwama. I've been hired to clear out the infestation to help re-balance the colony. I'm also required to defeat a large kwama warrior who guards the queen."
"I accepted a mission to scout Castle Roebeck for the Pact."
"Kill the Red Rook Spy before he can report to his superior."
"I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Lumbermill  for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Dragonclaw Lumbermill for the Dominion."
"Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars."
"Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the deadly greater hive golem they call Writhing Sveeth."

"Rogue Dark Elves flaunting the Pact are enslaving Argonians at a mine near Ash Mountain. A powerful Daedra rebelled against the mine's master. Then the Daedra took most of the people at the mine into Oblivion."
"Lord Diel of Daggerfall and his sons are investigating the recent harpy attacks all along the coast. They hired a group of mercenaries called the Daggers to help them with their research
"InternalName": but the Daggers never returned from the Shrieking Scar."

"Journal": "Sister Alarvyne would like me to collect Mountain Tail to use in tea she makes to soothe the blighted."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Farm for the Dominion."
"A Breton shipbuilder named Jeromec Lemal has asked me to help him recover the warship designs from three ships under construction in the docks at Tava's Blessing."
"I've agreed to help the Hermaeus Mora cult of Primeval Seekers to prevent the nereid of Halcyon Lake from using forbidden secrets to subvert the laws of nature."
"I accepted a mission to scout Chalman Lumbermill  for the Covenant."
"Varo Hosidias of Cyrodilic Collections wants me to enter the Tsofeer Cavern and gather any pieces of Imperial armor I can find for the benefit of a benefactor named Tia Doran."
"I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Mine for the Covenant."
"I've found a strange glowing artifact from the age of the Altmeri deep within the ruins of Bewan."
"The scholar Nendirume warned me that the Scaled Court has taken over the ruined city of Skyreach. She believes they're searching Skyreach Hold for more of the nirncrux element
"InternalName": which they refer to as \"the blood of Nirn.\""

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Warden Farm for the Pact."
"Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the dangerous cliff strider they call Old Stomper."
"A runner arrived from Fort Morvunskar
"InternalName": an installation to the west. Thane Mera believes Fildgor's forces have launched an attack against the fort."

"Journal": "Brengolin
"Zone": needs some assistance in creating some unconventional cuisine. This time he's asked me to procure him some Bosmer Root Liqueur."

"Journal": "I volunteered to enter the ruined crypts beneath the fort to look for the retainer
"Zone": and the mysterious others mentioned in the General's dispatch. The entrance is by the river."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Mine for the Pact."
"I've reached the siege range. Bugbesh told me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Marc and Jaleel to learn more about the weapons."
"Garnikh bet his axe that I can't best the Seamount hunters in duels."
"Heimlyn Keep is under a terrible curse. A group of Covenant soldiers attacked
"InternalName": thinking they were assaulting a military target. Instead they loosed an ancient magic hidden beneath in the vaults."

"Journal": "Thorkan is worried that Normar's rumors of necromancy in Fell's Run will cause bloodshed between Orcs and Bretons. To keep the peace
"InternalName": he wants to stop to the necromantic rituals and put Normar's fears to rest."

"Journal": "Proctor Sovor Saryoni
"Zone": is dying and has asked me to help save his life. He believes his only hope to continue his existence lies in an experiment conducted by a former apostle
"ZoneID": but she was exiled long ago because of it."

"Journal": "The wizard <<1>> in Davon's Watch told me his apprentice has stolen his spellbook. I offered to help find him
"InternalName": but there's a problem. To punish him for a previous theft
"Zone": the wizard changed the warding rune on the book."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Dragonclaw Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Farm for the Dominion."
"Gasteau Chamrond knows how to escape the structure I've fallen into. He'll help me get out if I lend him my strength."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Aleswell Farm for the Covenant."
"A glory-seeking Orc warrior asked me to help him gather ogre teeth for a trophy necklace from the battle. Why not?"
"Renzir
"Zone": was betrayed by his first mate Madja. He requested that I recover his trade shipments
column8: and find out what happened to his wife

"Journal": "General Godrun is counting on me to finish this battle with the Ironhand Ogres. If I can collapse the cavern they're using to get through the mountain
"InternalName": that should solve the ogre problem for good."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Fort Glademist for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Keep for the Dominion."
"I found a journal written by a priest of Z'en
"InternalName": which details part of Bloodtoil Valley's history. The local spinner may find this information valuable if I can find the rest of the journals."

"Journal": "The Reachmen attacked Shor's Stone and brought the giant Sinmur back to life. Now they've overrun Fallowstone Hall
"InternalName": an ancient seat of the Companions. Vigrod wants my help regaining the Hall."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Black Boot for the Pact."
"<<1>> of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Fang Lair."
"<<1>> led a mutiny against the captain and crew of the Albatross as they searched <<Ac:2>> for ancient treasure."
"Netapatuu and his colleagues came to Pinepeak Caverns to consult with the spirit of Hakra
"InternalName": one of Ysgramor's Companions. Worm Cultists attacked and drove them out. The cultists cannot be allowed to gain control of Hakra's spirit."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Farm for the Pact."
"The owners of the Dro-Dara Plantation have lost everything. First ogres attacked
"InternalName": and now bandits. The plantation was owned by a group of retired adventurers. The thief
"ZoneID": asked me to rescue the others."

"Journal": "A Gold Coast Trading Company ship was lured ashore by a powerful nereid. I've been hired to defeat the nereid and recover the cargo in the wreckage. She's protected by a group of sailors who she controls through a magical song."
"Clear the graveyard of zombies
"InternalName": making sure you check the crypt."

"Journal": "A note in Ilessan Tower has informed me that the Red Rooks are amassing resources for their allies. It also mentioned an attack on a manor north of Deleyn's Mill."
"The mysterious operative called Naryu has been investigating the evidence I discovered at the Maulborn camp."
"The Clan Murtag Orcs are fighting the Ironhand ogres in Shinji's Scarp. They've asked for my help."
"<<1>> has received word that more Dremora are entering the city from the north."
"The final battle against Angof begins now. I need to get inside and navigate the labyrinth of catacombs to find a safe place for Gabrielle and the soldiers to teleport into."
"Collect Wayward Branches for Alreal outside Elden Root."
"While in Silsailen
"InternalName": I learned that the imposters have taken real Auridon Marines captive."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Bloodmayne Lumbermill  for the Covenant."
"Adiel Charnis is distraught. Dreugh attacked her home in the Dreughside district
"InternalName": and her husband fought back. They wounded him and dragged him off toward their spawning pools. Adiel holds out hope her husband still lives."

"Journal": "After picking up an ancient sword in <<1>>
"InternalName": I learned an Ayleid knight's spirit haunts the ruins."

"Journal": "My actions have convinced Chief Tazgol to join the Daggerfall Covenant."
"Vampires occupy the Orchard beyond the Chasm
"InternalName": somehow empowered by Molag Bal's Harvest Heart. The vampires need to be dealt with before our forces can push forward toward the planar vortex."

"Journal": "Foreman Jomund discovered a mysterious metal in the mine. He hastily hid their research notes and the ore sample just as the Stormfists began taking over the mine."
"Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training."
"I found the body of a House Redoran soldier. He carried a medallion inscribed with instructions for his retainer
"I accepted a mission to scout Warden Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to scout Faregyl Mine for the Pact."
"I have completed the first part of the Two Moons Path with the Lunar Champion. Now we must venture into the Den of Lorkhaj and complete the mystical journey."

"Treasure-hunting pirates have disturbed the undead necromancers in <<1>>. Now the great seal that kept them trapped has been weakened and the necromancers may soon be free to threaten all of Hew's Bane."
"Outside the ancient ruins of Skyreach Pinnacle
"InternalName": I met a member of the Scaled Court. He told me that the Court accidentally released creatures from magical wards the Nedes set up long ago. He plans to reestablish the wards

"Journal": "The Dark Brotherhood has given me a contract."
"Concordia Mercius of Cyrodilic Collections needs my help to stop Margus Derius and the Blackguards from obtaining the Golden Skull of Beela-Kaar."
"The Mages Guild is investigating a strange Ayleid ruin
"InternalName": which has recently become much more active than in years past."

"Journal": "<<1>> uncovered information proving <<Ac:2>> is definitely located within <<Ac:3>>. She needs my help in recovering it."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Lumbermill for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to scout Fort Warden for the Covenant."
"Dralof Waterwalker and his friends bathe in the hot springs south of Wittestadr. Their friend
"Zone": went off to gather bath salts for the water

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Mine for the Dominion."
"<<1>> and his cohorts have taken up residence in Spindleclutch. <<1>> has returned to find his home overrun
"King Kurog has given me a standing invitation to drink with him at the King's Cornerclub in Orsinium. I seemed to have impressed him
"InternalName": and he obviously needs someone to handle the more delicate problems facing his kingdom."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Bloodmayne Lumbermill  for the Dominion."
"I wandered into a strange rift between the living world and the land of the dead. Here
"InternalName": I met the spirit of Sonya Lastblood
"Zone": who said that her husband killed her and her three daughters."

"Journal": "Arcady Charnis believes someone ordered men to plant dreugh eggs in the Dreughside neigborhood to cause the dreugh to attack."
"Queen Ayrenn must perform the final ritual at Tanzelwil in the ancestral crypts. Malicious spirits plague this holy shrine and the traitorous Norion lurks somewhere in the shadows."
"Abbot Durak took some Spirit Wardens up to the Cave of Dreams to find a way to deal with the largest fire in the fields. I should check up on them."
"I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Lumbermill  for the Dominion."
"Bandits attacked Pariah Abbey and set its crops on fire."
"Alchemist Nilyne Hlor doesn't trust the proprietary formula the Maulborn use to make their curative. She wants to examine a few bottles so she can determine how the elixir is made."
"I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Keep for the Pact."
"<<1>> asked me to deliver a message to his brother <<2>> in <<3>>."
"I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Lumbermill  for the Dominion."
"My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City."
"Bandits set fires in the fields to distract the Spirit Wardens. While the wardens were outside fighting the fires
"InternalName": the thieves stole a priceless relic: the Dream Shard."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Black Boot Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Farm for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Blue Road Keep for the Dominion."
"A Goblin tribe has invaded Cumberland's Watch. A soldier asked me to help fight them off."
"A moon priest named Thalinfar told me that I was needed at Fort Grimwatch
"Dreugh are mysteriously attacking the Dreughside district. Sergeant Stegine is organizing a defense. I should lend my aid."
"I accepted a mission to help capture any three keeps for the Pact."
"A few days ago some men attacked Jordel Trueblade and his family.  They killed his wife
"InternalName": took his children and left him for dead.  You must find his children."

"Journal": "The shoreline of <<1>> is lined with the shattered hulls of Aldmeri Dominion sailing vessels. Equipment and personnel are scattered along the beach."
"A Daedric creature is loose in Bonesnap Ruins
"InternalName": and <<1>> has found a way to contain the creature by repairing a Welkynd Stone that's been damaged by invading Goblins."

"Journal": "The Goblins attacked Cumberland's Watch because Captain Rama raised their sacred totem over one of the towers as a challenge. Commander Kurt has sent me to take it down."
"An army of Withered Hand soldiers necromancers attacked Tava's Blessing and killed everyone. Whatever they are planning here
"I accepted a mission to help capture Roebeck Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I found an injured Spirit Warden in Pariah Abbey's fields. Falice Menoit said she was attacked by Midnight Union outlaws. She'll be fine
"InternalName": but she's worried about others who were injured in the attack."

"Journal": "Now that I've retrieved the Dream Shard
"InternalName": I can finally return it to the Spirit Wardens at Pariah Abbey."

"Journal": "I've helped the community leaders of Bleakrock Village. Rana's preparing the villagers to evacuate."

"Slavers are using Steelheart Moorings as their base of operations and they're holding some sailors who they recently captured. The first mate has asked me to help free the sailors from the slavers' clutches."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Arrius Farm for the Covenant."
"After I returned the Dream Shard to Pariah Abbey
"InternalName": Abbot Durak told me of concerns that Vaermina also works to destabilize the eastern region of Gavaudon. I'm to warn High King Emeric and then meet Durak at Shinjis's Scarp."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Black Boot for the Covenant."
"The Divine Prosecution has requested I defeat the gryphons Haeliata and Nagravia. I'll also need to collect their feathers."
"I accepted a mission to scout Arrius Mine for the Pact."
"The Sea Drakes have captured friends of <<1>>. They're being held at <<2>>."
"Nojaxia wants to join the Mages Guild in Ebonheart. She's trying to create an elixir that replicates the visions an Argonian receives after licking a Hist Tree."
"Supernal Dreamers have attacked the Vanne Farm and captured the owner
"Zone": with the intention of subjecting her to some dark ritual."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Keep for the Dominion."
"Walks-Softly wants some more of my help with the situation involving his old friend
"InternalName": Anais Velmont. The letter he left indicates he's come up with a solution that he wants to run by me."

"Journal": "We've taken control of the Shrouded Pass and the way to the Doomcrag is open. The time has come to make our final assault and reach Montclair and  the cursed relic known as the Lightless Remnant."
"Bandits are disguising themselves as Knights of the Flame and robbing people on the road to Wrothgar. I promised Sir Graham I'd get the tabards back."
"Cyrodilic Collections' operation in Murkmire is growing
"InternalName": and more explorers mean more mouths to feed. With my help
"Zone": Jee-Lar plans to send cured meats to Black Marsh."

"Journal": "I met the Wood Orcs of <<1>> in <<2>>. They have come under attack from raiders and gradually weakened by an unknown source. I should work with <<3>> to track down the source."
"A daedric cultist is summoning scamps in the vault directly west of King Faume's grave."
"I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Lumbermill for the Pact."

"The final assault to end the Planemeld is at hand. We need to fight our way through Molag Bal's defenses and reach the portal to the planar vortex. Only then can we end this threat and save our world."
"I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I arrived in the city of Vulkhel Guard
"InternalName": gateway to Auridon. Security is tight as Queen Ayrenn
"Zone": the new leader of the Aldmeri Dominion
"ZoneID": prepares to make a public appearance."

"Journal": "The Supernal Dreamers also took Ingride's daughter
"Zone": and they're apparently planning a similar ritual using her as the vessel for some daedric spirit. I promised Ingride I would stop them."

"Journal": "The Dark Elves and Argonians are finally willing to work with Prince Irnskar and meet in a council of war. Now the Prince wants me to convince the Eastmarch thanes to attend the war council as well."
"<<1>> of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Hircine's March of Sacrifices."
"I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Farm for the Dominion."
"The Worm Cult has invaded the ruins of Rulanyil's Fall
"InternalName": intent on raising an Ayleid warlord from the dead. <<1>> wants to ensure the body is not disturbed."

"Journal": "An Argonian named Onuja has come to Othrenis. He wants to know how to rebind the Brother of Strife. He's hoping to contact the spirit of Mavos Siloreth
"InternalName": an ancient Dunmer scribe buried in the area."

"Journal": "Though the Omen of Fear has been dealt with and Alcaire is free of its influence
"InternalName": Duke Nathaniel is concerned. He's asked me to go seek the counsel of a Spirit Warden named Muran-to see if he can explain what happened."

"Journal": "Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the island of Blackheart Haven in Iliac Bay."
"I am to summon and kill the Dremora that slayed the miners
"InternalName": then report to Brek after the deed is done. The artifact to summon it should be near the tower on the hill. I can navigate through the mines to find a way there."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Mine for the Pact."
"The city of Evermore is in dire straits. King Eamond is dead
"InternalName": and a Reachmen army marches toward the city gates even now. The people of Evermore need help

"Journal": "Followers of Hermaeus Mora have come to secure the ancient Ayleid ruins at Lake Halcyon
"InternalName": but they say a mysterious entity inhabiting the ruins has enslaved local villagers and is trying to subvert the laws of nature."

"Journal": "Before he died
"InternalName": I met an Orc named <<1>>. He belonged to a holy order that lights Malacath's pyre once every decade
"Zone": but was ambushed before he could do so. I swore to head to the heart of Old Orsinium and light Malacath's pyre."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Zimmeron is ordering Pact soldiers to capture the <<1>>."
"The Sentinel Docks have been overrun with undead and the guards don't appear to be doing anything in response. I told Captain Marck I would try to find out what's going on."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Drakelowe Lumbermill for the Dominion."

"The nereid of Halcyon Lake is trying to save the lake from eventually drying up by using ancient and forbidden secrets to create a Water Stone. Hermaeus Mora cultists called Primeval Seekers are trying to stop her
"InternalName": but I've agreed to help her."

"Journal": "So-and-so has asked that you do something cool. Won't you do something cool."
"I found a note on the charred corpse of an assassin who was sent to kill a mage named Malsia. She stole Dwarven artifacts and plans to open a portal to someplace. The Mages Guild wants her dead."
"Angof's Bloodthorn cultists threaten the Wyrd Tree. I should help the Beldama Wyrd save the tree."
"The only way to ensure Evermore's security and drive the Reachmen from northern Bangkorai is to defeat their leader
"InternalName": the Hagraven Uela. I have agreed to help the Wyresses in Jackdaw Cove toward this end."

"Journal": "Shark's Teeth Grotto has been overrun by pirates and Shalug needs some help dealing with them."
"The Orsimer army needs to get into Frostbreak Fortress to find and destroy the source of the briarheart warriors
"InternalName": but the Winterborn's defense are too strong. Between the briarhearts and the harpies

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Black Boot Farm for the Pact."
"Velatosse is suspicious about the plague's origins. She's asked me to look into the source of this mysterious illness."
"The Reachmen at Jackdaw Cove are corrupting the spriggans and transforming them into monstrous lurchers."
"An old Redguard sitting in the desert is contemplating fate. He believes all of our actions are predetermined."
"I accepted a mission to scout Rayles Mine for the Dominion."
"The assassin Naryu Virian must kill a Dark Elf noble in Kvatch to fulfill a contract for her shadowy organization. However
"InternalName": she doesn't want to attract the attention of the Dark Brotherhood as she completes her work
"Zone": so she asked for my help."

"Journal": "<<1>> says some mercenaries in Stormhold are stirring up trouble between the Dark Elves and Argonians."
"So and so has asked that you travel to the big red box and do some stuff!"
"I accepted a mission to scout Castle Alessia for the Pact."
"Hallin's Stand is under the control of the Seventh Legion
"I accepted a mission to scout Warden Mine  for the Dominion."
"Yarah needs to discover the identity of whomever betrayed Hallin's Stand and allowed the Seventh Legion to enter the city."
"<<1>> has expressed concerns about events unfolding at Alcaire Castle. She asked me to go there and see if I can help."
"I accepted a mission to scout Castle Faregyl for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Lumbermill for the Pact."
"I found a letter on the body of a bounty hunter. It mentions a woman named Wardiya in Bruma."
"Falinesti Summer Site is a legendary seasonal location for the Wood Elves' Walking City. But the city hasn't been seen in Tamriel for centuries. Now
"InternalName": something is happening at the Summer Site."

"Journal": "The Council of Province Generals has ordered an investigation into the death of the former Guildmaster
"If I can show that I know how to make a ring
"InternalName": Felarian will certify me as a jewelery crafter."

"Journal": "Supernal Dreamers stole a crystal from Geoffrey Stictal and broke it into multiple pieces. He wants me to retrieve the pieces from them."
"Ufa the Red Asp and I must work together to locate the traitor identified by Captain Dhakir's men in order to save the grandeya of Hallin's Stand from execution."
"<<1>> has come to <<2>> to find out why the Drublog attacked Velyn Harbor."
"Cultists called Supernal Dreamers are up to no good in Moonlit Maw. Master Muzgu
"Zone": led other monks here to stop them. But they were ambushed by the cultists."

"Journal": "<<1>> does not believe <<2>>'s story about <<3>> becoming infected. Something isn't right."
"The Supernal Dreamers performed a ritual on Muzgu that infused a Daedric spirit into his body. He's contained it for now
"InternalName": but it's gaining strength. If the spirit takes control of him
"Zone": it will combine its powerful magic with his own. Many will die."

"Journal": "The Drake of Blades' contact in Legion Zero has not checked in for weeks. The Drake has requested that I go try to establish contact myself."
"I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Mine for the Pact."
"An army of undead swarmed from the sea and attacked the Sentinel Docks. Watch Captain Zafira has asked me to inform King Fahara'jad."
"Dominion soldiers erected barricades around a tribe of Argonian refugees living in <<c:1>>. <<2>> needs help resolving the Argonians' situation."
"Prince Azah says the necromancers of the Withered Hand are tunneling into the Impervious Vault to steal powerful relics known as the Ansei Wards. We must try to stop them."
"I discovered the Cliffs of Failure
"InternalName": where Molag Bal's failed servants compete to get back into his good graces. Lost members of the Mages Guild have been ensnared in this twisted game
"Zone": and I need to join in to save them."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help re-capture Fort Rayles for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to scout Aleswell Farm for the Pact."
"I met a talking monkey in Sentinel. The monkey claims he's really an Orc and that he was tricked by a Khajiit potion-maker named Unishi. He wants to be changed back."
"The Red Rooks attacked a caravan and escaped to a noble's house on the outskirts of Daggerfall
"InternalName": where they've taken hostages. Captain Farlivere of the Daggerfall Guard has ordered her soldiers to surround the estate."

"Journal": "The hamlet of Moira's Hope has met with disaster. Bloodfiends fill the streets
"InternalName": and the few survivors that remain are trying desperately to stay alive. I agreed to help Adusa-daro provide aid and find out who is behind this attack."

"Journal": "The Withered Hand has taken over Tu'whacca's Throne and begun using the Ansei Wards to raise the consecrated remains of fallen heroes. I agreed to help the Throne Keeper activate defenses to cleanse the temple."
"The dead have risen at Tu'whacca's Throne
"InternalName": and an Ash'abah here is particularly worried that three ancient heroes have been raised. I agreed to visit their graves
"Zone": and if they have been raised

"Journal": "I met a man named Beryn in the woods
"InternalName": recovering from an epic drinking bout at his camp. He's worried because he fears his friend <<1>> has wandered into a nearby spider cave on a dare."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Dragonclaw Farm for the Pact."
"I received an invitation to celebrate a festival of fools and foolishness across Tamriel."
"I encountered a captive Dark Elf soldier named Saryvn in the ruins beneath Tal'Deic Fortress. He was captured by the Maulborn while he was avoiding his duties."
"The Throne Keeper and I have lit the sacred braziers at the cardinal points of the temple. When we light the final brazier
"InternalName": Tu'whacca should send his \"Breath\" to come and help us cleanse the temple. Then we can kill Uwafa and recover the Ansei Wards."

"ZoneID": has returned to Skyrim. Nords from the Stormfist clan
column9: have infiltrated the Konunleikar to get close to King Jorunn."

"Journal": "A band of notorious criminals known as the Blackguards are searching for a powerful Argonian relic called the Remnant of Argon. I'll need allies if I'm going to find it first."
"Captain Kaleen's cabin girl
"Zone": informed me that Kaleen's crew is ready to start the heist as soon as I'm done recruiting."

"Journal": "<<1>> was the sole survivor of the Bloodthorn cult's attack on the Aldcroft lighthouse. She asked me to retrieve her father's pipe from his cottage so she will have something to remember him by."
"Throne Keeper Farvad says I should continue my search for the remaining Ansei Wards in Bergama to the east."
"I discovered a Spinner named Melrethel imprisoned in the cellars of the Vile Manse. She claims to be from the Wood Elf village that Graccus razed and built his manor upon."
"The scholar's apprentice Shiri has studied a book from among Alasan's possessions. Shiri suggests I begin my search for the third Ansei Ward in HoonDing's Watch."
"People are disappearing from the streets of Bergama
"InternalName": and I've decided to help investigate the matter."

"Journal": "With <<1>> dead-again-and the new Silvenar revealed
"InternalName": <<2>> asked me to head to <<3>> in <<4>>. The Aldmeri Dominion needs to prepare for the wedding between the Green Lady and the newly-discovered Silvenar."

"Journal": "Onsi's Breath was captured by Imperial soldiers who hold its inhabitants captive."
"I found Lord Geoffroi's son trapped in a cage."
"Once the mines were a prime spot for prospectors
"InternalName": but with the influx of spiders
"Zone": they've been shut down for safety reasons."

"Journal": "The Bursar of Tributes seeks items of flesh to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard."
"A caravan was attacked by snakes at the oasis near Ogre's Bluff. The caravan guard is afraid of snakes and asked me to return and help the members of the caravan."
"The spirits of HoonDing's Watch have awoken to test me. I must vanquish the spirits of the Redguards' ancient foes and claim their essence to summon their leaders."
"Kozanset
"InternalName": a small settlement in the deserts of Alik'r

"Journal": "Shiri
"Zone": has disappeared along with the text she recovered from Tava's Blessing. I've agreed to help find Shiri  and the text."

"Journal": "<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Auridon."
"Imperial forces have seized control of Satakalaam. King Fahara'jad's army is here to take the city back
"InternalName": but General Thoda needs to rescue four hostages the Imperials are holding first."
a New Life Herald in Eastmarch
"Zone": spoke of the New Life Festival celebrated across Tamriel."

"Journal": "The Withered Hand stole the Ansei Wards
"InternalName": ancient swords that protect Alik'r from necromancy. King Fahara'jad has asked me to enlist the aid of the Ash'abah
"Zone": a tribe of dishonored warriors who fight the undead."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Warden Lumbermill  for the Dominion."
"<<1>> of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Malabal Tor."
"In the Wayrest graveyard
"InternalName": I found the last Will and Testament of a scholar named Frodibert Fontbonne. Frodibert challenged his son Donel to solve a riddle to claim his inheritance. Donel gave up
"Zone": but maybe I can solve the riddle."

"Journal": "Serge Arcole asked me to help him incapacitate the smugglers. Then I'm to search the counting house for clues as to where Miranda's being held."
"The Prophet contacted me through a magical projection. He asked me to seek out a place called the Harborage
"InternalName": where he has taken refuge. I should go to him and ensure that he is safe."

"Journal": "Serge Arcole says the Midnight Union is holding his wife
"Zone": for ransom. He wants me to collect some items and bring them to him so he can bargain from a position of strength."

"Journal": "Corpses are crawling out of the ground at Pelin Graveyard and taking up arms. Prince Adrien was to be entombed here."
"I accepted a mission to scout Castle Brindle for the Dominion."
"General Gautier believes his son Darien

"Journal": "Hara has decided it's time to do something about the third guardian
"InternalName": the Thief. The Thief has been mysteriously absent except for when she appears to speak to me in private."

"I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Lumbermill for the Pact."
"A Crown bride
"Zone": has been left at the altar because the Forebear groom
column8: hasn't shown up for the wedding. Both families are angry
column9: and I've agreed to help settle the matter."

"Journal": "The guardian star sign of the Warrior has failed to appear to protect the mortal world from the Serpent. One of the Star-Gazers needs help uncovering what might be happening."
"The elemental guardian asked me to head for the Wyrd Tree. I need to find Wyress Gwen and help save the Wyrd Tree."
"The Mages Guild has researchers looking into the details surrounding the way Faolchu originally died. It happened at an ancient battle site called the Glenumbra Moors."
"<<1>> has challenged me to explore the White-Gold Tower in the Imperial City."
"A Khajiit named Ildani was apparently caught trying to smuggle her wares into Sentinel. She's asked me to help her recover the confiscated goods."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Farm for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Rayles Farm for the Covenant."
"A bored member of the Queen's entourage let me know Her Majesty plans to speak soon in the city of Vulkhel Guard."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Farm for the Covenant."
"While wading through the swamp
"InternalName": I stumbled into a cloud of roaming poison gas and passed out. Two Imperials rescued me and asked me to help them clean it up."

"I accepted a mission to help capture Chalman Farm for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Farm for the Covenant."
"Knights of Arkay search for holy relics to help combat the rising undead threat spreading throughout Rivenspire. So far

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Farm for the Covenant."
"Battlereeve Tanerline charged me with finding allies to attack the abyssal geysers and destroy the pearls that power them before the Sea Sload cabal's plan to sink Summerset comes to fruition."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Sebazi in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Alessia Farm for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Farm for the Covenant."

"I accepted a mission to help re-capture Fort Glademist for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help re-capture Fort Ash for the Covenant."
"I found a letter from someone named Iocundus in <<1>>."
"I accepted a mission to help regain Fort Dragonclaw for the Covenant."
"The Sapiarchs of Lillandril imprisoned a member of the Mages Guild. The authorities are convinced this mage murdered one of Lillandril's sapiarchs
"InternalName": but the particulars seem murky. There may be more to this murder than meets the eye."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Faregyl for the Covenant."
"Arch-Mage Valeyn believes I'm here to help protect the Academy against some unnamed threat. While he determines what this threat is

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Roebeck for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Brindle for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Glademist Lumbermill for the Covenant."
"I was bitten by a vampire. I have the option of embracing the disease or receiving the cure."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Ash Lumbermill for the Covenant."
"The guardians wait inside the Wyrd Tree
"InternalName": ready to assist me against the <<1>>. Once the <<1>> is destroyed

"I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Lumbermill for the Covenant."

"I accepted a mission to help capture Bloodmayne Lumbermill for the Covenant."
"After the cave collapsed
"InternalName": I found myself in a strange ruin. A spectral image appeared before me
"Zone": a woman named Oriandra. She says she wants to help me get out of this place."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Warden Mine for the Covenant."
"I found a dead adventurer in Barrow Trench. They entered the mine to collect rare ingredients for an alchemist in Woodhearth."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Rayles Mine for the Covenant."

"I accepted a mission to help capture Kingscrest Mine for the Covenant."

"Zone": believes the ogres of Wrothgar possess a misunderstood artistic genius. He wishes to create a replica of ogre artwork for the House of Orsimer Glories."

"Journal": "I have been welcomed into the bizarre realm of the Daedric Demiprince Fa-Nuit-Hen. In order to test my mettle and demonstrate my skills
"InternalName": I've agreed to enter the Maelstrom Arena
"Zone": where deadly challenges created by Fa-Nuit-Hen's Barons await me."

"Journal": "Ancalin
"Zone": asked me to pray at the grave markers of her four children. She hopes my travels around the island will give them some peace."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Farragut Mine for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Blue Road Mine for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Faregyl Mine for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Roebeck Mine for the Covenant."
"I met a mer named <<1>> near the ruin known as Quendeluun. He claims the Veiled Heritance took his daughter. He tracked them to the site."
"I accepted a mission to help capture Brindle Mine for the Covenant."
"Roguzog
"Zone": wants to settle a grievance with a High Elf named Lirendel. We'll have to learn all the rules and customs of High Elf dueling before Roguzog can get bloody satisfaction."

"Journal": "If <<1>> is to prove herself worthy of leading the Aldmeri Dominion to glory
"InternalName": she must complete the ratification ceremony in <<c:2>> of <<3>>. Legends say it can reveal those worthy of becoming emperor  or empress."

"Journal": "I stand with Captain Darien Gautier and the rescued Camlorn citizens. The time to retake Camlorn from Faolchu has arrived."
"After we thwarted the Imperial plot in Evermore
"InternalName": Uela the crow paid me another visit to say we're enemies again now and that her Reachmen army is going to kill everyone in Evermore."

"Journal": "With Honrich Tower secure
"InternalName": <<1>> asked that I seek out <<2>> in Taarengrav. The tomb holds one of Ysgramor's great companions and must be protected from the Worm Cult."

"Journal": "<<1>> said that the Wyrd Tree will recover
"InternalName": but another danger has appeared in the north."

"Journal": "Geoffroi has asked me to kill Remelie Frinck
"InternalName": the Fire Mage leading the Supernal Dreamers."

"Journal": "A contingent of Shornhelm Guard soldiers was on patrol when it was attacked by House Montclair troops. The Guard survivors have taken refuge in an old tower on Hinault Farm
"InternalName": where they continue to be under siege by Montclair's forces."

"Journal": "An Aldmeri Dominion fleet was shipwrecked here by a hurricane. I wasn't part of the wreck
"InternalName": but perhaps I can use the chaos as cover."

"Journal": "In the wake on an Imperial attack
"InternalName": homes are on fire and Daedric creatures are shambling through the village."

"Journal": "The Divine Prosecution seeks able-bodied adventurers to assist with the enforcement of laws by performing contract work throughout Summerset."
"The Khajiit
"Zone": has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted."

"Journal": "The Red Rooks have taken over the Crosswych Mines
"InternalName": turning the miners into slaves. Further
"Zone": anyone who resists them are sent into the mines as prisoners."

"Journal": "I came across a dead body on the path to the Everfull Flagon. The dead body clutches a note."
"While exploring
"InternalName": Lady Clarisse Laurent mistakenly opened a portal allowing Aldmeri Dominion soldiers to invade the ruins of Salas En. I've agreed to help her close the portal."

"Journal": "I stumbled onto the ruins of a campsite by the beach. Sea Drakes attacked and kidnapped two people last night."
"Battlemaster Rivyn has challenged me to win three Battleground matches."
"<<1>> has been trapped in Sanguine's celebration for four years. He's convinced he can only escape if the other party goers are distracted by an entertainment troupe from Morrowind."
"I returned from the past with the knowledge we need to defeat Faolchu. Fire weakens him and makes him vulnerable."
"I discovered an Orc imprisoned in the dungeons below Salas En. He claims to have lived there for centuries
"InternalName": kept alive by Aldmeri enchantment. The stones of his prison glow with mysterious energies."

"Zone": lost her guar and a valuable ruby to crocodiles in the swamp. She's too hurt to round them up
"ZoneID": so she asked me to search for the ruby and her favorite guar

"Journal": "<<1>> turned up again in Ebonheart looking to collaborate on another \"business venture.\" He wants me to procure a bottle of <<2>> from an innkeeper."
"Produce around Cropsford is not being harvested. It's going to go bad unless something's done soon."
"Something is definitely happening at Fort Amol. Groups of high-ranking Nords
"Zone": and Dark Elves are on hand
"ZoneID": and the guards are turning travelers away from the inn. I should try to figure out what's going on."

"Journal": "I encountered an injured Lion Guard knight named Sir Malik Nasir in Merovec's Folly. He wants to stop the Bloodthorn cultists from desecrating the dead Lion Guard soldiers."
"I encountered the spirit of Richard Dusant
"InternalName": who died searching for the hidden treasure of Dresan Keep. He wants me to finish his search for the Keep's ancient secrets."

"Journal": "Kassandra
"Zone": entered a second xanmeer called Vakka-Bok. Famia and I must enter this vast ruin and prevent Kassandra from acquiring the Remnant of Argon."

"Journal": "With Vox's wards shattered
"InternalName": the path to her lair is open. Aspera the Forgotten suggests this creates an opportunity to defeat Vox
"Zone": but I'm not sure I can trust this strange projection."

"Journal": "Alanwe lives a tortured existence in the Crypt of Hearts. Her soul has been shattered
"InternalName": and the pieces strewn throughout the Crypt. I have promised to help her."

"Journal": "Soldiers from Evermore were defeated at Murcien's Hamlet by a Reachman attack."
"The Shrine of Saint Veloth has been desecrated by Magistrix Vox. This Daedric attack has left the spirit of Veloth in a weakened state."
"<<1>> says the Crosswych resistance has gained enough momentum. It's time to deal with the Red Rooks' leader
"King Dynar has devised a two-pronged attack to take control of the Reaver Citadel. It utilizes the old Fighters and Mages Guilds' halls located in this ancient Nirn city."
"A Redguard named Hadoon believes ones fate is not predetermined. He believes one can break from destiny but needs help proving his theory."
"The Vosh Rakh attacked Fharun Stronghold
"InternalName": killing people in Trinimac's name. A dying archivist claimed they sought a secret sanctuary and the sacred words of Malacath that are hidden within."

"Journal": "Lord Geoffroi Stictal wants the shards of his Crystal of Power back so his wizard can repair it."
"Darien discovered that we need three shard-keys to open the three locks that protect Angof's inner sanctum."
"Hildegard never returned to the Sanctuary after going out to pray for Tanek. Kor asked me to help him find her."
"<<1>> is plagued by wisps. They're stealing away travelers at the gravesite. No one is sure what caused their sudden aggression."
"I met a miner named Samsi at the Badwater mine. She tells me that the mine is collapsing and her partner is trapped inside. I told her I would go in and find her partner. If he's dead
"InternalName": she still needs his supply pack."

"Journal": "In the tangled paths of <<1>>
"InternalName": I found the bodies of a Lion Guard officer and his patrol."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers."
"The Shade of Prince Naemon and the Veiled Heritance have somehow raised the infamous warriors of the Blackroot Clan from the dead."
"The Worm Cult is performing a ritual at an altar somewhere in the Smokefrost Peaks."
"Torinaan's strange little relic-keeper worries the holy relics will be corrupted by Daedric energies."
"Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the cavern called Spindleclutch beneath Glenumbra."
"I found the journal of Graccus
"InternalName": an Imperial who destroyed a Bosmer village to find a treasure buried below."

"Journal": "Rumors are floating around that the Thieves Guild isn't a threat anymore. The Thieves Guild wants to quash the rumors with a series of conspicuous thefts."
"I met Titus Valerius in Belkarth. He was hoping to find Kelmen to assist him and the Thief with a ritual to locate a magical disturbance near Skyreach
"InternalName": but the mage is nowhere to be found."

"Journal": "A Lion Guard patrol on its way from Daggerfall to Wayrest was attacked by Daedric Cultists who referred to themselves as 'Supernal Dreamers'. The cultists kidnapped the guard captain."
"<<1>> just learned that he inherited an estate. Unfortunately
"InternalName": the estate appears to be haunted and is overrun by imps."

"Journal": "I found <<1>> within the tunnels of <<2>>. She claims she and her husband
"ZoneID": at the behest of an Orc named <<4>>. She managed to escape
column8: but needs help rescuing her husband."

"Journal": "Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training."
"<<1>> of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Grahtwood."
"I found a note on the body of an Ebonheart Pact soldier. It mentions an egg brother named Bosekus in the town of Cropsford."
"<<1>> knows his monks cannot defend <<2>> against a determined assault from the Kasgesh Ashlanders. He's asked me to appeal to the Tribunal for aid."
"A mysterious Khajiit named Hunal spoke to me outside of the city of Dune. He told me some important task awaits me at the temple known as Moonmont."
"A Covenant officer and her husband attempted to defect to the Aldmeri Dominion. Covenant troops pursued the Orc couple all the way to Auridon
"InternalName": and they've taken North Beacon in an attempt to capture the Orcs."

"Journal": "Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe
"Zone": wants me to go to Bok-Xul and accomplish the task he set before me."

"Journal": "<<1>> requested I gather a magical substance from the runestones in Clockwork City. I'll also need to collect a special crystal that causes the residue to glow."
"<<1>> wants me to take word of our accomplishments to Hissmir."
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "A spirit named <<1>> warned me of dark knowledge sealed in three forbidden tomes. She asked me to find all three and destroy them in a shrine on <<2>>."
"An associate of Cariel's stopped me outside of Arenthia to ask for help. She's lost some critical supplies and letters
"InternalName": and wants my help in retrieving them."

"Journal": "Destroying the cursed skull held by the Shademist vampires has cleared the moors of corruption
"InternalName": but Thorinor says his wife was among the missing and never returned."

"Journal": "The herd of guar at the sulfur pools stampeded during the Covenant attack. Now they're scattered. If I can calm them and fit them with the proper harnesses
"InternalName": the animals should return to the stable on their own."

"Journal": "A naked Nord stands frozen in place in the wilds of Vvardenfell. He claims a Dark Elf witch cast a spell on him
"InternalName": and only she can remove it. He asked me to find her and get her to set him free."

"Journal": "I met an apprentice to Divayth Fyr in Vivec City
"InternalName": she mentioned an incident at her master's tower involving some kind of rift."

"Journal": "A strong Covenant raiding force landed west of Ebonheart. The citizens are too busy with their own internal squabbles to unite against invaders. <<1>> fears the town may fall to Alexandra Conele's forces."
"Drublog Orcs attacked the village of Tanglehaven. <<1>> said the survivors barely managed to fend them off. After the massacre
"InternalName": the surviving Tanglehaven militia chased the Drublog into the forest-including <<2>>
a New Life Herald in Eastmarch
"Zone": spoke of <<2>>'s New Life Festival in Shadowfen."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Farm for the Pact."
"I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Farm for the Pact."
"<<1>> has been taken captive by the Goblins
"InternalName": and Fafnyr was wounded in the fighting. The Nord warrior seeks revenge against the hated Goblins and their spider allies."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Farm for the Pact."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil."
"Ra'shadda
"InternalName": the Khajiiti shaman who summoned the monster
"Zone": didn't leave the plantation. Ruvali speculates that he wanted to stay behind to watch the monster tear them apart."

"Journal": "<<1>> tells me his son
"Zone": has gone missing somewhere in the oasis near Bergama."

"Journal": "A Red Rook messenger was captured near the Dwynnarth Ruins Lion Guard camp while he was on his way to a secret meeting between the Red Rooks and the Bloodthorn cult."
"Tanval Indoril has fled towards the Tormented Spire with the Coral Heart in hand. He wants to unleash Sadal
"Zone": from his imprisonment. Kragenmoor's <<1>> is the only one who can allow me access to the mountain."

"Journal": "Defeating the Dark Witnesses can only be accomplished by killing the Hagraven
"InternalName": Uela. Some of the Wyrd Sisters up near Jackdaw Cove have been searching for where Uela is hiding

"Journal": "An eccentric Argonian by the name of <<1>> asked me to help her fulfill a dream of hers
"InternalName": somehow involving creatures called swamp jellies."

"Journal": "Lady Clarisse Laurent and her man-servant Stibbons
"InternalName": along with a number of research assistants on loan from the Mages Guild
"Zone": have been studying the ruins of Bal Fell. Now
