"ZoneID": everyone but Lady Laurent has disappeared."

"Journal": "<<1>> asked me to help slow the Covenant's siege of Davon's Watch."

"King Fahara'jad has informed me of dire circumstances in Bangkorai. King Eamond is dead and the Reachmen are marching on the kingdom's capital of Evermore. He has asked me to go there and try to rally the city's defenses."
"Furon is worried that his brother Giron has joined a \"circle of mages.\" He wants my help to understand what they're doing."
"I met a man who had a wife
"InternalName": said he would keep her all his life. The one day he met a girl."

"Journal": "Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Tempest Island
"InternalName": a storm-tossed outcropping off the coast of Malabal Tor."

"Journal": "Covenant forces have scaled the walls of Davon's Watch. Now they're threatening to take the city from within its walls. Tanval's ritual may be our only hope to end the assault."
"Imperial archers are preventing rebel troops from crossing the river."
"Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore Selene's Web
"InternalName": a spider-haunted grove in Reaper's March."

"Journal": "With the Covenant driven from Davon's Watch
"InternalName": <<1>> has asked me to return the living weapon known as Balreth to its cell."

"Journal": "The remnants of a broken siege lie outside Davon's Watch
"InternalName": broken by the appearance of an army of ghosts. A sergeant at the front
"ZoneID": has asked me to decide how best to deal with the spirits."

"Journal": "With the Colovians removed from the village
"InternalName": Captain Odreth has planned a counterattack with his Rangers. We are to use a secret tunnel to gain access to the Colovian camp and take them out."

"Journal": "Covenant troops have killed Captain Hjolm of Fort Arand
"InternalName": and they're threatening the safety of the recruits within the fort. Captain Llaari hatched a plan to respond to the threat."

"Journal": "A volcanic eruption and an infestation of shalks have devastated the town of Senie. The townsfolk are wounded
"InternalName": but distrust between Dark Elves and Argonians delay efforts to heal them."

"Journal": "Even though they're dead
"InternalName": Ix-Utha's Argonian brethren still act as slaves to the risen Chimer. They've returned to serve their cruel spectral masters."

"Journal": "<<1>> runs a finder's business and uses the Thieves Guild to track down his quarries. Helping him will surely reflect well on your skill as a thief

"<<1>> is grateful the dead have been put to rest. She wants to give of herself to restore the Starved Plain. She's proposed a sacrifice from herself and her students that will allow plants to grow again on the plain."
"<<1>> lost most of his kwama in a mine collapse. He asked me to help round up the survivors and convince them to return home."
"<<1>> continues to restore the long-lost reputation of Orc cuisine. She needs additional rare ingredients for a special dessert."
"Svanhildr wants to break the Oathbound offensive once and for all."
"I encountered a tormented Dark Elf spirit in the Orc camp at Malak's Maw. She asked for aid in easing her torment."
"Healer Ravel asked me to collect Saint Veloth medallions. As long as the monks are allowed to pray in peace
"InternalName": the medallions allow the power of the Tear of Saint Veloth to keep the Llodos plague in check on whoever wears one."

"Journal": "I met a confused Nord named Norgred on the road outside of Quarantine Serk. He said he was escorting a witch. Apparently
"InternalName": she turned on him and stole a valuable axe. He's anxious to get it back."

"Journal": "I awakened the spirit of an ancient Dark Elf scribe named Mavos Siloreth. Mavos's spirit can't remember how he bound Balreth in the original ceremony. To help me
"InternalName": he's going to perform a ritual and show me a vision of the past."

"Journal": "Bala
"Zone": is searching for her deceased lover
column8: he was part of House Dunmer
column9: so their status kept them apart. They promised each other to unite in death

"Journal": "A scout sent by Centurion Gjakil has found me near Fallowstone Hall. The scout reports Reachmen movement near <<1>>."
"Covenant soldiers are massing within Softloam Cavern. It won't be long before they have the numbers to launch an attack on Kragenmoor and the rest of Stonefalls."
"I've learned all I can at Othrenis. Onuja says that Balreth is somewhere near Ash Mountain. <<1>> has led many Pact soldiers there with hopes of containing the Brother of Strife."

"I need to rebuild my army if we're going to have any chance of confronting Molag Bal and stopping the Planemeld. The mysterious Groundskeeper suggests I rescue as many people as I can and send them to the Hollow City."
"Netapatuu fears the Worm Cult may try to enslave Valdur's spirit
"InternalName": much as they tried with Hakra's."

"Journal": "<<1>> sent me into a deep vision with the help of an ancient ritual site. In this vision of the past
"InternalName": I should be able to interact with Balreth and Sadal. Then I can learn how the Brothers of Strife were born."

"Journal": "Leel-Vata asked me to rescue the captured Argonian villagers from the Khajiiti pirates."
"<<1>> senses that a powerful Daedra has wrested control of the animals. As long as the Daedra remains
"The lands of the mighty Hrogar are overrun with Goblins and spiders. The Nord has lost many men to the beasts
"The Covenant has seized Fort Virak. They're serving under the command of General Serien. The Pact's army-led by the Indorils
"Zone": and Walks-in-Ash-has besieged the fort in an attempt to retake it."

"Journal": "I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "I've infiltrated the ruins beneath Fort Virak. <<1>> asked me to help secure our foothold within the fort's main courtyard."
"Fort Virak is ours. All that remains is to kill General Serien
"InternalName": the leader of the Covenant forces in Stonefalls."

"Journal": "Teldur has kidnapped Canonreeve Valano and taken him into the manor."
"<<1>> warned me that Tanval will likely try to release the second Brother of Strife from Tormented Spire. To ascend the spire I'll need to speak to the grandmaster of House Dres in Kragenmoor."
"The Omen of Betrayal failed to manipulate General Godrun into attacking Wayrest
"InternalName": but has now trapped General Godrun within his dream. Abbot Durak has asked me to enter the dream and kill the Omen to save Godrun."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a bonus for any Pact soldier who slays 40 enemy combatants."
"I've helped the survivors at Heimlyn Keep. Now I need to end the curse. Its mystical corruption emanates from a Telvanni reliquary."
"<<1>> has been having problems with rats down his well."
"Verandis completed his research and discovered that his missing memories lead to an ancient ruin in the Lorkrata Hills. He needs my help to discover the secret hidden within the ruins."
"<<1>> fears for the survival of the Hist Tree the Argonians transplated from Black Marsh to Ebonheart. He thinks the Dark Elves of House Dres poisoned it
"InternalName": so he wants to fertilize it to encourage its growth."

"Journal": "Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to delve the Banished Cells beneath Auridon."
"A frightened soldier on the road told me about a slave revolt at Sathram Plantation. Ulov Stormwall led troops to the plantation
"InternalName": intending to suppress the revolt. Mysterious circumstances induced him to turn his blade on his own troops."

"Journal": "I found a note on a dead Khajiit with plans for the riot. Apparently
"Zone": followed by the freeing of prisoners."

"Journal": "I met a strange Imperial who was being held captive by the Daggerfall Covenant. He believes he knows how to defeat the cursed army of Anka-Ra that has laid siege to Craglorn since the Celestials appeared."
"Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to brave Fungal Grotto in the caverns beneath Stonefalls."
"An extremely angry Argonian named Azeenus has asked me to seek vengeance against the Khajiiti pirates in his name."
"Dragons have not been seen in Tamriel for generations
"InternalName": and the Khajiit are unsure how best to fight against them. The ancient Nords recorded Dragon fighting techniques on scrolls they keep in their crypts. I need to find these scrolls."

"Journal": "Farseer Bodani has placed the fate of Raston Vendil in my hands. I agreed to undertake a trial and see if the Ghost Snake will counsel me on this matter."
"Minister Ralden and Giron are missing. Advisor Varon believes that Giron is working with the Maulborn and has abducted Ralden."
"Clanmother Shuzura has apparently been very hard on her assistants. There are problems in the little town of S'ren-ja. Perhaps I can help out."
"Noxious fumes have leaked into Deepcrag Den
"InternalName": a kwama mine. The workers fell ill and the normally docile kwama became enraged."

"Journal": "Fildgor the usurper fled to the ancient dragonshrine of Skuldafn to steal Queen Nurnhilde's spirit and force the Crown of Freydis to recognize him. I need to stop him."
"I agreed to help Madras rescue the missing villagers. However
"InternalName": I need to prove myself to him before he'll tell me where they're being held."

"Journal": "Falkreath Hold is under siege by an army of Reachmen and minotaurs. It may well fall without outside intervention
"Councilor Ralden and Giron are missing
"InternalName": along with many villagers. Varon Davel believes Giron is working with the Maulborn. Apparently
"Zone": Giron abducted Ralden. I need to find them before it's too late."

"Journal": "I came across the wreckage of a trade caravan on the road between Mournhold and Narsis. Attacks on caravans don't usually occur this close to Mournhold
"InternalName": and the presence of a Dwarven construct makes this incident even more unusual."

"Journal": "The Covenant landed west of Ebonheart
"InternalName": but a band of Nord sawyers have refused to join the general defense. They sneeringly refer to the town's Dark Elves as \"fancy lads.\""

"Journal": "The vile sorcerer
"Zone": continues to terrorize the people of Wrothgar. He has raised countless Orcs as undead thralls and trapped their spirits in Mundus. I must set their spirits free and put this necromancer to the sword."

"Journal": "House Dres raiders and Dwarven constructs attacked a caravan carrying valuable cargo. The House Hlaalu noble who sponsored this caravan will want it back."
"General Gavryn Redoran is acting erratically and completely out of character. Something has changed. I get the impression that Tal'Deic Fortress is in some kind of trouble."
"<<1>> asked me for help in dealing with a personal matter."
"The Dunmer of Ebonheart have turned to <<1>> for comfort in the face of an expected assault by Covenant forces. Disciple Sildras
"Zone": believes the Tribunal has rejected the town. His gloom is affecting the citizens' morale."

"Journal": "The Covenant has taken Fort Virak
"I met a strange little man who requested that I engage him in a game. He proposes that I acquire three items from some of his fellow carnival members. Once I acquire the items
"InternalName": he will take one from me and turn it into something amazing."

"Journal": "<<1>> requested I gather herbalist's satchels which contain alchemical plants in Clockwork City. I'll also need to collect a sweet syrup to help subdue the bitterness of the tonic created from the satchel's plants."
"The Maulborn have occupied the Obsidian Gorge
"InternalName": the pass to Mournhold. House Hlaalu guards have cordoned off the area to keep anyone else from walking into a trap."

"Journal": "Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the powerful kagouti called King Razor-Tusk."
"Shadowfen's Vicecanons are concerned about the Dominion running supply lines for their troops through Alten Corimont."
"<<1>> has a plan to steal treasure from Dominion troops before they find out what happened to <<2>>
"Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ancient complex beneath Elden Root
"Due to archaic rules
"InternalName": <<1>> of the Aldmeri Dominion is allowed to undergo sacred Argonian trials at Hissmir. Success will allow him to commune with the Hist. To determine his true plans
"Zone": I must pass the trials myself."

"Journal": "I completed the Trials of the Burnished Scales at Hissmir
"InternalName": which allows me to commune with the Hist. Doing so will give me insight why Captain Henaamo

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Woodworker goods to an interested organization."

"Journal": "Someone stole several relics from a cart in Hissmir. I offered to help <<1>> find the culprit."
"A group of pilgrims failed to arrive in Hissmir as scheduled. <<1>> fears something has happened to them."
"I met a Breton in the middle of the swamps of Shadowfen. She seems to be lost."
"I received a voucher for a special-occasion cake from the renowned master baker
"It appears that soldiers known as Sentinels are terrorizing the fortress."
"Maj al-Ragath has challenged me to explore the kwama mines of Darkshade Caverns beneath Deshaan."
"I met Kothringi from <<1>> who told me Worm Cult necromancers plague their village."
"The town of Stormhold is plagued with murders and abductions."
"<<1>> wants me to look into the disappearance of <<2>>."
"<<1>> suspects the Dominion skin-stealers are based out of <<2>>."
"I've discovered where Grandmaster Omin Dres' son is being held captive. The Vanguard is holding his son
"Zone": in the tombs west of Kragenmoor."

"Journal": "A guar herder named <<1>> has lost control of his herd. Tanval's Vanguard drove them out of their pen
"InternalName": and Ral now fears for their safety."

"Journal": "The grandmaster of House Dres has given me a key that should see me past the wards at Tormented Spire. Now all that remains is to make my way there."
"Count Carolus still owes us what he promised for taking on his contract-information concerning the Black Dragon. Astara wants to find out what the Count knows."
"<<1>> is encamped at Trolhetta with the bulk of the Ebonheart Pact's army. The Worm Cult is dug in
"InternalName": and hoping to hold on until they can gather the shards of Wuuthrad for some nefarious purpose."

"Journal": "According to the Undaunted Trailblazer
"Zone": the ruins of Fang Lair have been taken over by a cult of necromancers who are preparing for something big. She's enlisted my help in discovering and foiling their plans."

"Journal": "The monastery of Muth Gnaar was attacked by the Vereansu
"InternalName": a violent tribe of Ashlanders. The peaceful monks were caring for the afflicted using an ancient relic called the Tear of Saint Veloth when the Ashlanders attacked."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a bonus for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy combatants."
"The people of Slag Town apparently seek predictions about the future from a factotum known as the Grand Prognosticator. Kamid
"InternalName": whose mother died during the last pilgrimage
"Zone": plans to prove that the oracle is a fraud."

"Journal": "Scout Kanat says that the rest of the scouting party is dead or afflicted
"InternalName": too far gone to be saved. He also says the Maulborn are protected from the Llodos plague by arcane wards."

"Journal": "Fleeing undead to the north
"InternalName": a clan of Bosmer refugees wants to settle in Shadows Crawl
column8: rose from the ground and attacked."

"Journal": "After returning the <<z:1>>
"InternalName": <<2>> made me the arbiter over the fate of <<3>>. Destroying the <<z:1>> will allow the villagers to die
"Zone": but preserving it will trap them in their lifeless state."

"Journal": "The scholar Nendirume warned me that the Scaled Court has taken over the ruined city of Skyreach. She believes they're searching Skyreach Hold for more of the nirncrux element
"InternalName": which they refer to as \"the blood of Nirn.\""

"Journal": "A traveling merchant named <<1>> fell prey to Worm Cult necromancers camped below <<2>>. His guards were killed
"InternalName": and their souls are now trapped in animus geodes throughout the cultists' camp."

"Journal": "I found the abandoned journal of Dulza
"InternalName": an Orc merchant who somehow entered the Clockwork City during a fierce storm in Craglorn. Her greatest regret is that her clan in Fell's Run will never see their ancestral sword again."

"Journal": "Churasu has a way to turn the giant wasps into an army to use against the Khajiiti pirates. She needs my help to make an alchemical concoction."
"After Drillk's memory returned
"InternalName": he told me how to obtain the keystone. It's locked away in the Temple of Sul."

"Journal": "Sibling explorers Raynor and Kireth Vanos are investigating the Dwarven ruins of Bthanual."
"I've found a book about Ayleid 'Alasil pilasters' within the Temple of Sul. Beside it was a small Ayleid relic that may be able to awaken the pilasters."

"I met a somewhat drunk and totally bootless Breton named Parquier Gimbert outside of Northpoint. He said he lost a valuable mace while hunting for mudcrabs along the shore. He thinks that maybe a Hagraven was involved. Also
"<<1>> has nearly restored the long-lost reputation of Orc cuisine. She needs a few more rare ingredients to complete her masterpiece."
"A Dwarven device fills a chamber deep within the ruins of Bthanual. Kireth has repaired it. Beams of light now shine through prisms set around the room."
"I met an artificer who's trying to learn more about the mysterious rod that was used to control Dwarven constructs from Mzithumz."
"<<1>> went to the <<2>>. He has yet to reply to <<3>>'s correspondence."
"I found a battered journal while walking the Coiled Path. A young woman named Risa did not survive this place. She lost her amulet fighting one of the snakes."
"<<1>> welcomed a traveling High Elf to <<2>>
"InternalName": but she believes he has something to do with the wisps' recent aggression."

"Journal": "To rid the area of her corrupting influence
"InternalName": <<1>> and I cleansed the ancient vessel. We need it capture the wispmother in <<2>>."

"Journal": "The Aldmeri Dominion has set up a staging area south of Hissmir in a fishing village called <<1>>."
"<<1>> led a force of Pact soldiers to Ash Mountain. They were following the Brother of Strife
"InternalName": Balreth. Using the information I learned from Mavos at Othrenis
"Zone": we're going to imprison the Brother of Strife again."

"Journal": "Raynor and Kireth Vanos
"Zone": left Morrowind to look for long lost knowledge and lore within Skyrim's Dwarven ruins."

"Journal": "The Ordinators are outnumbered. They asked me to reduce Vox's forces to help even things up a bit."
"Queen Ayrenn ordered the once-forbidden island of Summerset to open its borders and welcome outsiders to its expansive shores. Razum-dar
"Zone": has come to the island to make sure the decree is followed to the letter."

"Journal": "I've defeated Ash Mountain's guardians. Now I must enter Ash Mountain's caldera
"Scamps are boiling up out of the ground
"InternalName": no doubt excited by the freeing of Balreth. <<1>> asked for my help dealing with them. Collapsing the entrances to caves in <<2>> should do the job."

"Journal": "I left the ancient Argonian ruins with a single Fang of Sithis. According to <<1>>
"InternalName": the Renrijra pirates are in an uproar. They may be feeling the effects of the other Fang in their midst."

"Journal": "Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Fungal Grotto beneath Stonefalls."
"The Bursar of Tribute demands compensation for the Blackfeather Court from mortals who insult them and chase them away."
"<<1>> told me of an assault force landing in the Ashlands west of Ebonheart. She's asked me to make for the land coral maze known as Vivec's Antlers."
"Lord Stictal had a unique power crystal that was stolen by Supernal Dreamers. They have shattered the crystal in order to use the pieces for daedric summoning ritual."
"I have been tasked by Lord <<1>> to recover shards of a crystal of power from the Supernal Dreamers who have stolen it."
"A Bosmer scout claims her band was ambushed by Argoninan invaders. She managed to get away in the scuffle
"InternalName": but her allies are now captives of the Argonians."

"Journal": "I met a Dunmer named <<1>> in Apocrypha's Gate. He's a devotee of Hermaeus Mora. He and his fellows were attacked by rival cultists of Mehrunes Dagon
"InternalName": and their sanctum was put to the torch."

"Journal": "The Covenant attacked the Argonian town of Lukiul Uxith. The residents repelled the attack. They seem to be quite confident about their safety."
"Save Geoffroi's Son."
"I found a notice stating that adventurers looking for rewarding work should report to the Hall of Justice."
"Queen Ayrenn asked me to join her at the ancient site Tanzelwil where she must commune with the dead. She's worried there may be  complications."
"The son of Lord Strictal was taken captive by the Supernal dreamers."
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "The Supernal Dreamers imprisoned Steve Stictal."
"I arrived in Skywatch to find a festival in honor of the High Kinlady Estre in full swing."
"Harvey was attempting to steal back his fathers shards when he was captured. He needs help escaping."
"Mehdze the Maestro is on an exploratory journey into King's Haven Pass to research his next epic. Unfortunately
"InternalName": things aren't going according to plan."

"Journal": "Ledronor
"InternalName": a member of a hunting order called the Hounds
"Zone": asked for my help in hunting a troll."

"Journal": "The military has tracked Stral Blackthroat
"Zone": to Vernim Wood. When they arrived
"ZoneID": they found Worm Cultists performing dark rituals with his warriors."

"Journal": "I encountered a wounded Lion Guard member named <<1>> in the Bonesnap Ruins. He and his soldiers were sent to retrieve pieces of an artifact
"High King Emeric has arrived with the Lion Guard to help retake Bangkorai Garrison from the Imperial forces."
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "After retriving the crystal shards
"InternalName": <<1>> wants me to defeat the leader of the Supernal Dreamers."

"Journal": "I met a pair of Argonians
"InternalName": former slaves. They want revenge upon Betina Volek
"Zone": the last surviving descendant of the family that once owned them."

"Journal": "The laborers helping to rebuild Orsinium need supplies
"InternalName": specifically fresh meat. The hills and valleys of Wrothgar are typically filled with beasts to hunt
"Zone": but their numbers are dwindling due to poaching. I must help feed the city's workers."

"Journal": "The grandmaster of House Dres wants revenge against the Vanguard troops outside Kragenmoor. He's commanded me to slay their leader."
"Marcus has told me that he was captured by Supernal Dreamers. I have freed him."
"Teeba-Ja was a member of the Bitterhand Bandits
"InternalName": but when they became more violent
"Zone": she decided to leave. She wants to start a new life in Shornhelm."

"Journal": "<<1>> is struggling to understand humor. He heard a rumor about a sacred Dark Elf performance from the distant past."
"I found a strange device in the Dominion camps at <<1>>. The instructions for its use were signed \"Alchemist <<2>>.\""
"The Hedorans were killed by bandits. <<1>> has asked me to recover anything I find in the remains of their home."
"Varon asked me to travel to Mournhold. I should inform the Ordinators about the events at the Obsidian Gorge."
"Something caused the creatures in Xal Ithix's swamps to become aggressive and attack the villagers."
"Kotholl
"InternalName": a hired hand from the merchants' camp
"Zone": was ordered to guard three specific chests with his life. He states it would be bad for the contents to fall into the hands of the Maulborn."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Clothier goods to an interested organization."

"Journal": "Kidnapped Guy has been kidnapped."
"A Khajiit named <<1>> has disappeared at the notorious Hadran's Caravan. The people who love him are losing hope of seeing him again. They have turned to me for help."
"The Dominion established a foothold in the small town of <<1>>. The Argonian Shadowscales intend to take back the town by force."
"Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the complex of sewers beneath Wayrest
"InternalName": dead center in the region called Stormhaven."

"Journal": "The Argonians in Xal Ithix have been picking through trash piles. Now normally docile creatures from the swamp are attacking them."
"Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe
"InternalName": called the Naga-Kur in the Argonian tongue
"Zone": wants me to go to the Echoing Hollow and accomplish the task he set before me."

"Journal": "Rigurt the Brash
"InternalName": leader of the Expedition for Nord Cultural Exchange
"Zone": has asked for my assistance. I've agreed to trade a Nord book
column8: and relic for similar Dark Elf items."

"Journal": "I found a stolen item with the name <<1>> etched on it
"<<1>> wants to find out more about <<A:2>>. Until the vicecanons understand its danger
"InternalName": they can't root out the Dominion in Shadowfen."
"Zone": "SN V Cracking the Egg TMW HP"

"Journal": "The town of Arenthia has been occupied by a Colovian force. I've been tapped to help retake the city alongside a Khajiiti resistance force."
"I found a Redguard mercenary named Ragara near the entrance to Zehtswater Cave. Her band was bitten and carried off by Lamias."
"Some terrible catastrophe has befallen Selfora
"InternalName": and now hostile spirits overrun the place."

"Journal": "An Argonian outside <<1>> asked me to find his brother
"InternalName": <<2>>. He was in the nearby mine when Goblins overran it."

"Journal": "The Bursar of Tributes seeks items of flesh to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard."
"While in the Goblin camp
"InternalName": I found a Nord corpse clutching a runestone that bears the name \"Hodmar Iron-Kettle.\""
"Zone": "SN V Mud Tree to Mud Tree"

"Journal": "I found a set of robes in a bandit camp."
"Tanval Indoril is inside the Tormented Spire working to unleash the Brother of Strife. Tanval's Vanguard holds the approach. If we don't stop Tanval
"InternalName": he'll unleash Sadal and destroy Stonefalls."

"Journal": "<<1>> asked me to deliver orders to a rebel spy in Imperial-held Cheydinhal."
"A shady character named <<1>> contacted me at Davon's Watch. He said we could both profit if I \"procured\" a rare and expensive bottle of wine for him."
"Mystery surrounds Forsaken Hamlet. An Argonian tree-minder lies murdered at the edge of her village."
"The Dominion slaughtered the Argonians living in a small hamlet in Shadowfen. Only one remains alive to take his vengeance."
"I have defeated the champions of the three major divisions in Thizzrini Arena. Now I am ready to face Ishalga and become the Grand Champion of Thizzrini Arena."
"The time to confront Vox has arrived-but it seems that to defeat her
"InternalName": I need to die by her hammer. The Blessing of Veloth should protect me
"Zone": but can I return from the dead?"

"Journal": "With Tanval's help
"InternalName": we've lowered the final ward guarding the prison of Sadal
"Zone": the Brother of Strife. The mages who originally imprisoned Sadal linger on the Tormented Spire as spirits

"Journal": "Priest Dilyne asked me to close the Daedric portals that Vox opened within the shrine. All kinds of vile creatures are emerging from these blasphemous wounds in the world."
"Shadowfen's Vicecanon Hrondar sent Saervild Steel-Wind to Bogmother's ruins to collect Argonian relics."
"I discovered a battered Dwarven construct that seems to have killed its Imperial caretaker. The Imperial's notes imply that they are searching for something within the Dwemer ruin at <<1>>."
"The vicecanons tracked an ancient keystone to <<1>>. This artifact would be a major boon to Pact forces in <<2>>. However
"InternalName": the prisoners seem unwilling to negotiate directly with the vicecanons."

"Journal": "The keystone is located within the White Rose Prison Dungeon. I've agreed to find it and use it to free the prisoners here."
"I agreed to gather Red Mountain Ash for <<1>>
"InternalName": so she can make Nirnroot wine."
a former prisoner of White Rose Prison
"ZoneID": but her grieving spirit lingers on."

"Journal": "I've encountered a Covenant scout named <<1>> in <<2>>. She was captured by Imperials and has asked for my aid."
"While attempting to test a new spell
"ZoneID": into a female Goblin. The Goblin lass has been kidnapped by a local Goblin warlord named <<2>>."

"Journal": "The Guildmaster of the Fighters Guild wants me to perform a task for her."
"Sees-All-Colors has had Doshia's journal translated. From it she believes she may have discovered information relating to the mysterious Mortuum Vivicus."
"I received a contract from the Speaker."
"The wilderness of Stonefalls is filled with predators and hostile creatures. The citizens of the region would sleep better knowing the worst ones are dead."
"I've accomplished great deeds with Tanval Indoril
"Zone": and Walks-in-Ash. We've returned Tanval's Vanguard to the Ebonheart Pact
"ZoneID": and convinced the spirits of Tormented Spire to open Sadal's prison."

"Journal": "While exploring Hildune's Secret Refuge
"InternalName": I found a journal written by Nadafa. It tells the story of how she was seduced by a vampire. The journal mentions that her husband
"ZoneID": works in Northpoint at the cemetery and lives in the fishing village."

"Journal": "This is the Talking Quest.  The purpose of this quest is to talk to people and things
"InternalName": to  make sure the conversation system is still working.  Tally-ho!"

"Journal": "Guildmaster Sees-All-Colors has plans to make use of the crystal and tome we found in the depths of Mzeneldt."
"I purchased a strange statue from an Ashlander merchant in the wilderness. It may be a religious fetish."
"Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights."
"Researchers seeking ancient relics around the xanmeers found Renrijra pirates camped in the Argonian ruins they were planning to search."
"The artifacts buried beneath Sunscale Strand are dangerous. <<1>> warns that we may have trouble with them. I need to be careful when searching the ruins."
"I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Blacksmith goods to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I found the ruins of a city called Shada's Tear in the middle of the Craglorn desert. A mercenary told me that some researchers from Belkarth went into the ruins
"InternalName": but that strange things started happening when they did."

"Journal": "Deshaan's Academy of Magic
"Zone": trains only the most promising mages to become leaders of the Ebonheart Pact. However
"ZoneID": the Academy only accepts those who've received a special invitation."

"Journal": "Dominion troops invaded <<1>>'s village
"InternalName": trapping her husband and the other villagers. Whatever the soldiers are doing in <<2>>

"Journal": "I found Minstrel Idria's lute abandoned in the Grotto of Depravity."
"Aamela Rethandus needs healing supplies to treat Selfora's wounded."
"<<1>>'s husband <<2>> won't speak since his ordeal with the Dominion. I must find a way to heal him."
"Arch-Mage Valeyn thinks his visions are somehow connected to the evil Magistrix Vox. Unfortunately
"I've put a stop to the threat of the Reachmen
"InternalName": but the threat to the Rift is far from over. The Worm Cult is massing in force
"Zone": and the settlements west of Nimalten need to be warned."

"Journal": "<<1>> tracked the Dominion's movement to <<2>>
"InternalName": where she hopes to end the Dominion invasion of Shadowfen."

"Journal": "<<1>> asked me to retreive <<A:2>> from <<3>>
"InternalName": the architect of the Dominion invasion in Shadowfen."

"Journal": "I uncovered evidence linking important community members in Mathiisen to the Veiled Heritance. Now Raz has asked me to take the fight to them directly."
"<<1>> is one of the few surviving prisoners from the Dominion's march into Loriasel."
"<<1>> wants me to look for his friend
"Zone": who seems to think he's a Goblin."

"Journal": "<<1>> asked me to find his son who hasn't returned to the village."
"A talking crow claims to represent the Blackfeather Court. It says I must pay a toll to pass safely through the court's domain."
"I received a voucher for a special-occasion cake from the renowned master baker
"A high-ranking member of the Mages Guild
"InternalName": <<1>> wants me to perform a task for her."

"Journal": "I've traveled to Shor's Stone
"InternalName": which is under attack by Reachmen. The Companions and Pact military have marshaled a defense."

"Journal": "I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "I've breached the barrier to the mine beneath Shor's Stone. The Reachmen have assaulted the foreman and his crew. I need to find the foreman
"Zone": and figure out what the Reachmen are doing here."

"Journal": "An ancient Argonian settlement called Haj Uxith occupies a dark corner of Coldharbour. The Argonians want to help me in my quest
"InternalName": but they seem to be divided over something related to their Hist tree."

"Journal": "Some of the miners beneath Shor's Stone still live!"
"While exploring <<A:1>> I came across a campsite with an inscribed vase. The inscription read as if it was given to someone
"InternalName": but I only found skeletons in the tomb."

"Journal": "The residents of Treva's Farm have fled. A Worm Cult attack drew the attention of nearby giants. The besieged farmers ran for their lives."
"The sky over the bardic college of Skald's Retreat is something out of nightmares
"There are tomes scattered across the islands of Skald's Retreat that all have something to do with Vaermina."
"The Celestial Warrior is worried about his champion
"Zone": Titus' memory has begun to break apart. He no longer remembers who he is or his connection to the Warrior. Without his memory
"ZoneID": the Warrior can't send him home."

"Journal": "The city of Riften has been devastated by Sinmur's assault. The town guard is overwhelmed trying to help all the refugees. They're asking everyone to help with the recovery effort."
"The Wood Elves in this part of the Valenwood are opposed to the Dominion. I agreed to negotiate and attempt to convince them to swear allegiance to Queen Ayrenn."
"<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Alik'r Desert."
"The Crystal of Power has been stolen and shattered
"InternalName": and  Geoffroi wants me to help him retrieve it."

"Journal": "I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "I'm helping Geoffroi restore his Crystal of Power. The Supernal Dreamers have stolen and shattered his Crystal of Power into five pieces."
"I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver food and drink to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I met a noble
"Zone": who's power crystal was stolen by the Supernal Dreamers and broken in 5 shards."

"Journal": "Distraught noble Geoffroi's antique crystal was stolen by Supernal Dreamers and split it into shards for their daedric rituals."
"Geoffroi's son has been kidnapped by Supernal Dreamers. I need to make sure he gets back safely."
"I was tipped off about a stash of Daedric treasures ripe for the taking in the Deadhollow Halls. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved
"InternalName": so I should act quickly on this lead."

"Journal": "I'm helping a young man escape from captivity. The Dreamers have chained him in a cage."
"Vvardenfell promises new experiences and new adventures. I can't wait to see what the land of the Dark Elves has in store for me."
"I found a guy tied up in a cage. He wanted to be free."
"I met a prisoner held by the Supernal Dreamers
"InternalName": who asked that I set him free."

"Journal": "Captain Erronfaire is desperate to leave port
"InternalName": but she's lost track of some of her crew. She needs them found so she can set sail for Velyn Harbor."

"Journal": "A thief named <<1>> needs a partner for a difficult job. I took her up on the offer."
"I guess I should let this guy go."
"Geoffroi wants me to murder the leader of the supernal dreamers."
"<<1>> and some of his inn workers were meeting a trader to restock supplies when pirates invaded <<2>>. Everyone scattered
"InternalName": and now his workers are lost in the marsh."

"Journal": "Julia Kalere has told me that I must kill the Twilight Boss to put an end to this madness."
"Geoffroi has asked me to kill Remelie
"InternalName": the leader of the cultists. This should send them fleeing back to Stormhaven. She should be near one of the Dreamer camps."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I need to kill the Beast to stop the Dreamers once and for all."
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "Troggg has discovered that it was his brother
"The slavers have captured the crew of a ship that crashed on the rocks. <<1>> has asked me to free them."
"I've been tasked with finding another book for the Mages Guild. Once again I need to return to the Shivering Isles
"InternalName": to a place called the Chateau of the Ravenous Rodent."

"Journal": "<<1>> of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Alik'r Desert."
"The Reachmen are being magically augmented by the Worm Cult. They must be stopped."
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts. There are no stipulations regarding methods or timing
"InternalName": so I may execute the target at my discretion."

"Journal": "Maulborn cultists are causing trouble throughout Deshaan. Quarantine Serk was only the beginning. A House Hlaalu guard asked me to take word of what happened to Narsis
"InternalName": a town south of the Serk."

"Zone": gave me a challenge to complete in Orc's Finger Ruins

"Journal": "Boulderfall Pass has been attacked by Sinmur and the Reachmen. The soldiers defending this area need my help."
"<<1>> of the Mages Guild wants me to recover a dangerous relic from Bangkorai."
"A dying soldier named <<1>> has asked me to avenge his death."
"I met a Redguard named Paldeen
"InternalName": held prisoner by the Khajiit bandits in the Lost City of the Na-Totambu. He asked for my help in opening the sealed inner chamber."

"Journal": "Magister Vox stole an item of power from the Tribunal Temple-the hammer known as Veloth's Judgment. She fled east
"InternalName": away from Mournhold. Almalexia asked me to track her down before she gains the full power of the artifact."

"Journal": "Rigurt the Brash
"Zone": presides over the Ebonheart Pact's diplomatic mission to Wrothgar. But Rigurt has a problem. He's fallen in love with his Orc counterpart

"Journal": "Our final goal at Vernim must be to kill Stral and end the threat of the Reachmen. Unfortunately he's protected by a death shroud in the central ruin."
"I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts
"InternalName": which requests the indiscriminate slaughter of citizens of East March."

"Journal": "A researcher named Nila feels terrible about her colleague's capture. The Worm Cult was torturing him at the far end of the cavern."

"Zone": asked me to join the expedition to <<2>>. They'll be searching for Argonian relics."

"Journal": "I received a contract from the Speaker."
"I'd been told previously Ulrich
"Zone": died at the hands of the cultists. <<1>> believes he may actually be imprisoned somewhere within Silaseli instead."

"Journal": "My first trial in Sheogorath's realm awaits. Valaste and Shalidor have uncovered what they need to get me where I need to go."
"I've encountered a wounded hunter in the wilds near Bleakrock Village. <<1>> is seriously wounded. He wants some help killing his prey."
"A strange woman came up to me as I was walking through the woods. She said something about skeevers before leading me into the hills."
"<<1>> is running low on supplies to help the many wounded in his care."
"I met up with Seyne near Hozzin's Folly. Bandits have landed on the island. They're exploring an abandoned mine that was once home to Daedra worshippers."
"The drunken cook
"Zone": is in trouble. She bet her hunter friend that she'd collect ingredients from beasts all over Shadowfen and cook him a feast in Hissmir. Now sober
"ZoneID": she is afraid to venture out into the fen
column8: for fear of these same creatures."

"Journal": "I found a Fighters Guild camp where an Argonian soldier is recovering from a fierce battle with spiders."
"The powerful Telvanni mage
"Zone": teeters on the brink of death. Now her replacement
column8: rules Vos with an iron fist. The situation seems dire."

"Journal": "The Daggerfall Covenant has assaulted Bleakrock Village. Captain Rana sent the surviving refugees to Last Rest
"InternalName": a tomb near the town. Rana and I must clear a path through the tomb for the refugees."

"Journal": "I caught up with Darj near Skyshroud Barrow. Skeletons attacked and wounded him before he could find a way to get its door open."
"I met a group of Dunmer in the Fungal Grotto. They want to reach a shrine within the caves. A tribe of hostile Goblins has occupied most of the area
"InternalName": pushing out a colony of dreugh. The two fighting sides are blocking access to the rest of the cave."

"Journal": "I've agreed to deliver a sack of fertilizer for <<1>>."
"Someone calling themselves The Rat left a note claiming that the Daedra are slaughtering people in the Imperial Arena. If I slay the Daedra
"Zone": The Rat promised to reward me with a secret about Molag Bal's plan for Imperial City."

"Journal": "Rolunda came to Orkey's Hollow looking for her brother
"InternalName": Eiman. The cave is said to be haunted
"Zone": and young Nords on the island sometimes enter it to prove their bravery. Eiman went in

"Journal": "<<1>> continues to restore the long-lost reputation of Orc cuisine. She hired me to collect additional rare ingredients throughout Wrothgar."
"I found a note on a dead bandit. Their leader
"ZoneID": so he can trade them for supplies."

"Journal": "Valaste and Shalidor have finished analysis of Sheogorath's books. Now I need to help them take possession of Eyevea
"<<1>> has lost track of her husband and her dog. I've offered to help her look for both of them."
"Outside the school of blades called Rahni'Za
"InternalName": I encountered an intiate of the school who told me that the Sword-Disciples have been turned into thralls by a traitor. This betrayer now hides in the cavern at the end of the school's five trials."

"Journal": "I've found evidence that the Daggerfall Covenant may soon attack Bleakrock and the rest of the Pact. We need to evacuate as soon as possible
"InternalName": but anyone who doesn't rally to the village will be left behind."

"Journal": "Giants have attacked the village of Lower Yorgrim
"I met Ibrula
"InternalName": a friend of the Star-Gazers who is trying to get into a ruined temple called the Seeker's Archive. She hopes to discover information inside that will help defeat the Celestials."

"Journal": "The Covenant sent an advance force into Bal Foyen. They're destroying the fields behind Dhalmora."
and Prisoners"
"ZoneID": I came across the Tower of Lies. Instead of a tower
column8: the place is actually a hole in the ground where members of the Fighters Guild have been imprisoned."

"Journal": "The Gnisis Egg Mine has been shuttered. Some kind of mysterious illness has taken hold there. Unfortunately

"We've landed safely. Captain Rana is going to muster the remaining Bleakrock villagers and the people of Dhalmora. She wants me to ensure the fires are lit in the nearby watchtower so we can warn Davon's Watch
"An Argonian named <<1>> lost most of his guar herd. They were spooked by scary noises in the fields behind Dhalmora. He wants me to collect the missing ones."
"I've made my decision. I'm standing with <<1>> and defending Fort Zeren."
"The Daggerfall Covenant has siezed control of Foyen Docks. An injured Argonian fisherman saw Rana fighting through their ranks."

"Stormfist soldiers ransacked Voljar's Meadery and slaughtered the family-all because they wanted free mead. Haraldar's wife was one of the Voljars killed in the attack. He wants to reopen the meadery
"InternalName": and he recruited his four brothers to help."

"Journal": "Maormer pirates took the lighthouse at South Beacon and are signalling more pirate ships to come into port. If they're not stopped
"InternalName": they'll have the numbers they need to move on the port of Vulkhel Guard."

"Journal": "Yraldar Snowpeak was wounded trying to drive the Stormfist soldiers away from the meadery. He wants their leader
"Zone": dead and his head on a pike. He asked for my help."

"Journal": "A merchant in Nimalten claims his silk was stolen by bandits. I've been asked to retrieve it for the angry businessman."
"<<1>> thinks he's found a way to use the otherwise docile netch against the Daggerfall Covenant."

"I returned to Dhalmora. All of the Bleakrock villagers are gone. Aera informed me of a large Covenant attack on Bal Foyen. Darj has lead some of the non-combatants to Fort Zeren. Captain Rana is leading a defense of the docks."
"After giants and wolves overran the village of Lower Yorgrim
"InternalName": the survivors found shelter in a tiny fishing camp outside the village walls."

"Journal": "<<1>> says that Shadowed Path cultists have taken over Haynote Cave
"I should head to Davon's Watch
"InternalName": so I can ensure the troops have been warned about the Covenant."

"Journal": "Nisin Cave is now a danger to Vlastarus. Shadowed Path necromancers and a Dremora named <<1>> have taken up residence."
"<<1>> of the Divine Prosecution requested assistance in curbing a growing reef viper population threatening Summerset's mainland."
"Praxin and his comrades from the Fighters Guild explained that spiders infest the Spindleclutch caves. And maybe something else. It whispers in the darkness."
"<<1>> wants an Imperial lieutentant killed
"InternalName": to hurt their army's morale and readiness."

"Journal": "I accepted the Fighters Guild contract Arkas offered."
"The Nord soldier Droi burns with fever from a witch's curse. I need to collect a plant called Kyne's Breath to help reduce his fever."
"The Keepers of the Kynesgrove shrine have become Daedric witches. The loss of their loved ones to war has made them lash out against Kyne. I need to find a way to resolve this."
"<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Rivenspire."
"I arrived in Eastmarch
"InternalName": in the Nord city of Windhelm. The place bustles with revelers as a celebration honoring the Skald-King is underway."

"Journal": "<<1>> has asked that I travel to <<2>> and inform his brother <<3>> that his wife is dead."
"The pirate captain Crafty Lerisa has come to Kvatch to convince her sister
"Zone": to abandon the Society of the Dragon
"ZoneID": a cult headed by the Grand Chanter of the Akatosh Cathedral for believers not ready to commit to the priesthood."

"Journal": "Thane Mera has named me the Champion of Windhelm and wants me to enter the Footrace of the Nine Holds."

"InternalName": the guildmaster of the Abah's Landing Thieves Guild
"Zone": believes someone sold out the guild to the Iron Wheel. She needs my help to deal with the matter."

"Journal": "Thane Mera
"InternalName": enraged by the death of the racer Hadring
"Zone": demands that the assassins pay for this crime. She wants me

"Journal": "A renegade clan of Nords known as the Stormfists launched a surprise attack against Fort Morvunskar."
"<<1>> says a skeleton invaded Vlastarus a few days ago. She thinks it came from a graveyard to the southwest."
"Firsthold is under assault by High Kinlady Estre. The First Auridon Marines have arrived to try and save the city
"InternalName": but the city is overrun with Daedra and the castle proper is surrounded by a magical barrier."

"Journal": "A giant bear named <<1>> has been attacking travellers near Vlastrus."
"The Dreamwalker is lost in King Jorunn's nightmares. I must enter the Dreamstride and try to rescue both of them before the Daedric poison kills the King."
"An Argonian named Bishalus is afraid that nix-hounds have devoured her friend
"InternalName": Gena. She claimed to have made a flute that could tame the beasts
"Zone": but she has yet to return."

"Journal": "Refugees fleeing the war were often preyed upon by bandits. Many of their possessions were stolen on the way to Vlastarus."
"The Skald-King and the other Ebonheart Pact leaders have established a base at Jorunn's Stand. While the Skald-King recovers
"InternalName": the leaders need to decide how to deal with Fildgor Orcthane."

"Journal": "<<1>> wants to neutralize the Gold Coast mercenaries in Malabal Tor so his people will be safe from reprisal."
"The sentry captain
"Zone": keeps the camp secure. She asked me to help."

"Journal": "The orders from Fildgor Orcthane suggest that the Stormfists are after something precious in the royal tomb. The spirit of Queen Nurnhilde and Lieutenant Koruni both asked me to return the relics. While I'm at it
"InternalName": I'll see what else is going on."

"Journal": "I need to halt the Daedric invasion from Moonhenge."
"<<1>> needs couriers to make deliveries around <<2>>."
"Rock Bone Goblins have made camp to the northeast of Vlastarus."
"<<1>>'s family banner has been stolen. He believes it was taken by bandits who visited Vlastarus."
"The Dominion took <<A:1>> to the Ayleid ruin of <<2>>. There they used its power to sever the Argonian connection with the Hist. As long as it remains in their possession

"A scholar by the name of Tharayya is searching for an elusive artifact hidden somewhere within the ruins of Garlas Malatar. She's enlisted me to help her deal with the hazards of the lost Ayleid city and recover her quarry."
"Deep inside a dungeon called Mehrunes' Spite
"InternalName": I found a scamp with a labeled choker. It apparently belongs to a mage in Skywatch."

"Journal": "To the east of Vlastarus lies Juras Falls
"I met a frightened young woman. Her and her friend were attacked by monsters on their way back to Windhelm."
"<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Malabal Tor."
"The Ebonheart Pact is at war with the Daggerfall Covenant and the Aldmeri Dominion for control of Cyrodiil.\n\nEveryone is needed in the war effort."
"Taralin says there is much more for me to learn about the war in Cyrodiil."

"A Daedric cult called the Supernal Dreamers stole a Crystal of Power from <<1>>.  The cult shattered the Crystal in five <<m:2>> and are using them in Daedric rituals.  <<1>> has asked me to kill the cultists and bring back the shards."
"<<1>> found out the Iron Wheel is planning to ship <<2>> to Taneth. As acting guildmaster
"InternalName": I've called on the Thieves Guild to do something about it."

"Journal": "Flame atronachs are plaguing the Ayleid ruins at <<1>>."
"I entered a secluded grove near Daggerfall Harbor called Bad Man's Hallows. The people here are engaged in a festival honoring the Bad Man
"I found a journal within the Mines of Khuras. It contained a message addressed to Odette Vinielle."
"<<1>> asked me to gather some silver scales for the local artist to use in her next project."
"The Supernal Dreamers have retaliated against <<1>> for having me steal back his Crystal of Power.  The Daedric cult captured him and threw him into a cage."
"I've found the temple of the spinners of Malabal Tor
"InternalName": where their \"story\" has gotten away from them."

"Journal": "Aspera Giant-Friend says the giants are about to go to war against the Stormfists that hold Cradlecrush because their mammoths were stolen. As long as I oppose the Stormfists
"InternalName": these giants will consider me to be an ally."

"Journal": "<<1>> told me his clan had a hand in the Silvenar's alleged kidnapping by the Hound."
"King Jorunn wants me to make my way to Skuldafn. He wants to deal with Fildgor Orcthane and then bring the rest of the Pact leaders to the ancient dragonshrine."

"InternalName": a Wood Elf down in the Bad Man's tunnels
"Zone": claims he is one of the mages that originally summoned the Dremora Lord now posing as the Bad Man."

"Journal": "In ruined Klathzgar
"InternalName": I found a note from an Altmeri scholar investigating an ancient mystery. An Ayleid princess named Urenenya vanished centuries ago
"Zone": and the scholar came here after learning of her connection to the Dwemer architect Klazthgar."

"Journal": "The Green Lady's sister
"ZoneID": a village famous for being the birthplace of several previous incarnations of the Green Lady as well."

"Name": "A Treasure in Need of a Home"
"Journal": "I found some ancient Nord relics. I'm sure someone will want to examine these. I'll take them with me and try to locate an interested party."
"The Worm Cult invaded Ouze and captured its primary protector
"Velsa left a note
"InternalName": asking that I come to visit her at her garden. She has something she wants to discuss."

"Journal": "The Worm Cult is trying to enslave the spirits of Ouze."
"Aspera and the giants are ready to begin the siege of Cradlecrush. Using the documents I recovered from the Stormfist scouts
"InternalName": they formulated a plan of battle."

"Journal": "I wandered into Cragwallow
"InternalName": a small settlement used by the Skald-King's royal work crews. After a lot of hard work maintaining the roads
"Zone": they're preparing to throw a party."

"Journal": "Lothgar Steady-Hand was grievously wounded by the creatures that attacked Cragwallow. He appears to be dying."
"Valeric believes vampires don't have to be monsters. He wants my help to stop his father
"Zone": who plans to create an army of bloodfiends."

"Journal": "The Banished Cells have been overrun by Daedra. They have set free the immortal High Kinlord Rilis
"InternalName": an evil being of great magical power. I have agreed to help Keeper Cirion
"Zone": the warden of the Banished Cells

"Journal": "<<1>> offered to tell me the story of the Green Lady and show me the most sacred sites of Deepwoods."
"Vicious raiders known as the Steel Shrikes attacked a troupe of traveling entertainers. They hold several performers captive at Fuller's Break."
"<<1>> wants to take his own type of revenge against the Steel Shrikes who destroyed his troupe's ship and livelihood."
"Jorunn the Skald-King has been poisoned. Now he lies in an eternal slumber. The Ternion monks
"InternalName": who revere the Three Old Gods
"Zone": attempt to cure him. But time is running out."

"Journal": "Inside the tombs of Skuldafn
"InternalName": I discovered that Fildgor Orcthane crossed into Sovngarde. To defeat Fildgor

"Journal": "Draugr have spilled from the barrow beneath Bonestrewn Crest. Now they roam the area
"Maormer Sea Vipers invaded Ilayas Ruins
"InternalName": searching for a weather-controlling relic called the Sphere of Storms. I've been asked to help the stormwardens defend the sphere until reinforcements arrive."

"Journal": "The Drublog clan of Wood Orcs captured <<c:1>>. I need to infiltrate Jathsogur and do whatever's necessary to free him."
"The Orcthane's troops have taken control of the mine in Lost Knife Cave. They're forcing the miners to produce ore to equip Fildgor's army."
"Maormer attacked an Aldmeri Dominion ship off the coast of <<1>> and captured several members of its crew."
"<<1>> asked me to burn the Maormer sailboats in <<2>> to prevent further ambushes."
"Worm Cultists have attacked <<1>>."
"Someone is stirring up chaos in <<1>>
"InternalName": and <<2>> asked me to help put a stop to it."

"Journal": "The people of Riften have been brought inside their shattered walls. While Sinmur is gone
"Zone": Riften's people may face other threats."

"Journal": "Though most of the rotmeth was stolen
"InternalName": an unfinished batch remains. <<1>> needs some special ingredients to complete what's left of the brew."

"Journal": "Jomund and his miners have no idea what to make of the mysterious metal they found. However
"InternalName": Jomund has a friend at Fort Amol who might be able to help."

"Journal": "The Ebonheart Pact has come together under King Jorunn's command to battle the Worm Cult at the ruins of Honrich Tower."

"Zone": told me that many Pact soldiers lie wounded around Honrich Tower."

"Journal": "Indaenir
"Zone": traveled across Malabal Tor to marry the Green Lady and fulfill his role as the spiritual leader of the Wood Elves. But the Hound arrived first and is trying to usurp his position."

"Journal": "People from across the Aldmeri Dominion gather to celebrate the handfast of the Silvenar and the Green Lady. The Hound
"Zone": caused many of them trouble. Among these are a group of minstrels led by <<1>>."

"Journal": "Rigurt the Brash has been named Master of Ceremonies for the celebration of King Jorunn's anniversary. Rigurt has many organizational duties to attend to and needs a little help."
"Lord Vivec's condition continues to deteriorate as his energy drains away. Archcanon Tarvus believes that Chodala's staff holds the key to saving the Warrior-Poet. However
"InternalName": it also makes the Ashlander practically impervious to harm."

"Journal": "After events in Shadowfen
"InternalName": Vicecanon Heita-Meen and I must travel to Eastmarch

"Journal": "I've arrived in Nimalten to find the city under threat. Thane Fjora was attacked by her houscarl. Aera Earth-Turner
"InternalName": my old friend from Bleakrock Isle

"Journal": "I've received a chilly welcome at Fullhelm Fort. The garrison is beset by undead
"InternalName": and the old Thane is not welcoming strangers."

"Journal": "A spinner in Valeguard wants to finally transcribe a story into written word

"Zone": asked me to help <<2>> investigate a number of murders in Stormhold."

"Journal": "Even though we've won a victory over the Worm Cult
"InternalName": <<1>> tells me that <<2>> is headed toward Riften. I should follow in the wake of the giant."

"Journal": "Thane Harvald want Lord Vurlop and I to go into the keep and check on King Jorunn. We need to make sure that the King and his war council are safe."

"Archcanon Tarvus agrees that Chodala is somehow involved in Lord Vivec's loss of power. He wants me to confirm his involvement and find a way to get his staff without starting a war with the Ashlanders."
"Preparations were completed just in time - the undead are attacking Fullhelm Fort! <<1>> has asked me to help defeat the attack."
"Lector Naril oversees the Everwound Wellspring
"InternalName": an oasis in the mechanical desert that is the Clockwork City. He has found a way to grow plants in the metallic soil. Once every year
"Zone": he shares his harvest and selects a new apprentice."

"Journal": "There's a coven of Hagravens in Northwind Mine. They need to die."
"Lieutenant Koruni asked me to deliver a dispatch detailing Fort Morvunskar's status to Thane Oda Wolf-Sister at Fort Amol."
"<<1>> of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Bloodroot Forge."
"The spirit Valdur worries about his fellow companion spirit
"InternalName": bound to Pinepeak Cavern. He's asked me to check on her."

"Journal": "Valdur spoke of a dark gathering at Honrich Tower."
"The Worm Cult has barred the route to <<1>>. King Jorunn has asked me to clear the way."
"We're almost there. We must fight through Worm Cultists to reach Sinmur and defeat him!"
"I've been hired to defeat the spirits which haunt Salothan Tomb."
"Ebonheart Pact soldiers carry amulets into battle
"InternalName": so they can be identified if they die. Collecting these amulets may bring solace to the families of the dead."

"Journal": "Redguard invaders attacked Velyn Harbor
"InternalName": while Drublog Wood Orcs entered the town from the hills. With the harbor's defenders either killed or scattered in the attack
"Zone": only a few Fists of Thalmor continue the defense."

"Journal": "The battle for Velyn Harbor continues. With a little luck and a lot of effort
"InternalName": the Redguard invaders and Drublog Wood Orcs can be driven from the town."

"Journal": "<<1>> isn't a resident of Velyn Harbor
"InternalName": but he's been caught up in their problems."

"Journal": "<<1>> hired Gold Coast mercenaries from Colovia to protect his tradepost
"InternalName": but suspects they will turn on him."

"Journal": "I've discovered a Worm Cult cell has come to the ruins of a Dragon Cult stronghold. No good can come of this."
"Someone extinguished Seyda Neen's lighthouse to cause a shipwreck. Deputy Governor Deminah Salvi suspects slavers and asked me to help her investigate the matter."
"Trolls overran the town of Darkwater Crossing and now the Argonians who lived there have taken refuge in a nearby cave."
"I have accepted a contract to defeat the creature Wraith-of-Crows and other Daedric incursions in Clockwork City's Radius."
"The town of Silsailen is under attack by imposters disguised as First Auridon Marines. The townspeople suspect these men and woman are a part of a group called the Veiled Heritance."
"Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Ebernanit and gather as many historic relics as I can find."
"Queen Ayrenn seeks to perform rituals honoring her ancestors. When she arrived at Tanzelwil
"Zone": she found the spirits angered and violent."

"Journal": "The Argonian Steady-Hand believes he's the best hunter in Eastmarch
"InternalName": better than any Nord or Dark Elf alive. He's challenged me to a hunting contest. If I can shoot a number of rabbits in one minute
"Zone": or catch the rabbit called Golden Jack

"Journal": "I received a voucher for a special-occasion cake from the renowned master baker
"In the ruins of Ezduiin
"InternalName": I found an enterprising researcher working with Telenger. She's concerned about the recent appearance of the spirits. She seeks a way to lay them to rest."

"Journal": "I found the journal of Orinol
"InternalName": a dead mage from the city of Cormount
"Zone": in Grahtwood. He arrived in Clockwork City by accident and died in the Radius sometime later. His dying wish was that someone would care for his dog

"Journal": "Two Weynon villagers were taken by the vampires of <<1>>. <<2>> fears they are dead and about to rise as bloodfiends."
"The Claw of Akatosh has been stolen from Weynon Priory by the Black Dagger gang. I've been asked to recover it."
"The Bursar of Tribute demands compensation for the Blackfeather Court from mortals who refuse to die so they can be pecked apart and eaten."

"InternalName": "An Altmer doing research in Treehenge found some cultists poaching mammoths at the shrine."

"Journal": "The Black Daggers are using an abandoned house west of Weynon to store supplies."
"<<1>> has asked me to travel to <<2>> and return <<3>> to rest."
"The garrison at Cey-Tarn Keep has been terrorized by a spate of unusual disappearances and deaths. A monster hunter named Silurie has enlisted my help to stop the killings."
"Geirmund's Hall hosts a festival
"InternalName": and Thane Vofknir is looking for brave souls willing to participate in an epic challenge. Those who pass the tests are named Geirmund's Guardian."

"Journal": "The warrior Daljari Half-Troll oversees the Trial of the Body
"InternalName": a test of brawn over brain."

"Journal": "Iroda
"InternalName": a member of the Thane's household
"Zone": proctors the Trial of the Mind. She's going to pose riddles to me. I need to seek out the answers to each on the island

"Journal": "A bunch of dumb
"InternalName": drunken bards have gotten themselves stuck in a giant camp near Ivarstead. They tried to charm the giants with music. Now I need to run over there and save them."

"Journal": "I met a Nord named Eirfa at Geirmund's Hall. She asked if I'd be interested in participating in a drinking contest. Let's see how this goes."
"Spies from the Aldmeri Dominion have infiltrated Sanguine's celebration. <<1>> gave me Sanguine's goblet and wants me to find the spies."
"<<1>> asked that I eliminate four flame atronachs issuing from the lava fissure in Chorrol."
"The town of Phaer is beset by a mysterious plague. The town alchemist
"Zone": has taken steps to treat the ill."

"Journal": "Lliae asked me to bring supplies to one of her caches out in Cyrodiil."
"Rigurt the Brash
"InternalName": an ambassador from the Nord Cultural Exchange
"Zone": came to Summerset to broker peace. Unfortunately
"ZoneID": he can't get an audience with the Proxy Queen."

"Journal": "I found a lost member of the Queen's entourage near the entrance to a hidden Vale. She told me that her fellow entourage members have been taken. A mad mage apparently holds them in the Vale."
"I need to test out a quest where someone reads two books. Fortunately
"InternalName": Jacques know where I can find them. He's lost
"Zone": but he knows where to find books."

"Journal": "This is the Background Journal Text"
"Svein fears that the fate of the dead in <<1>> will never be known to their families in Riften."
"Frostmoon Farmstead has been attacked
"InternalName": resulting in several grisly murders. Guard Jorald needs help uncovering the killer or killers."

"Journal": "Torinaan is a holy site dedicated to the Divines. It's been corrupted by Daedra. The loyal clergy there want my aid in cleansing the area."
"The Worm Cult is raising dead giants to fight Pact soldiers."
"Sage Svari has asked me to find and return <<1>>. She believes it's being held at Faldar's Tooth."
"The Bursar of Tributes seeks a particular treasure to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard."
"I met Arfanel
"InternalName": a member of the Eyes of the Queen at North Beacon. He's tracking an elite Covenant soldier and wants my assistance supporting the troops in the field."

"Journal": "Three friends have drunkenly wandered into the catacombs beneath Windhelm after having a good time at the Konunleikar. They won't leave the catacombs until they're reunited
"InternalName": but it's not safe for them to search the tunnels alone."

"Journal": "The farmer <<1>> requested my help in dealing with a glowfly infestation in his hay at Ivarstead."
"In the Hall of the Dead beneath Windhelm I met <<1>>. She plans to gain favor in King Jorunn's court by eliminating <<2>>
"InternalName": an ancient necromancer entombed in the Merethic Era."

"Journal": "I met an Argonian named <<1>> in the ruins of Quendeluun. She's asked me to help me secure her freedom."

"I arrived at a place called the College of Aldmeri Propriety. One of the students claims this Thalmor training ground heaps hardship and abuse upon the Wood Elf and Khajiit students. She's asked me to investigate."
"I've been taken to the secret island stronghold of the Veiled Heritance. If I can pass their trials
"InternalName": I may be able to discover the true leader behind the Veil."

"Journal": "My companions and I turned back the Daedric incursion into the Clockwork City and rescued Sotha Sil from his own shadow. Now
"InternalName": the Clockwork God has some wisdom to share before he leaves."
a member of a Pact scouting party
"Zone": barely escaped capture after discovering a hidden Lion Guard base in the mountains of the Rift. She needs a distraction to buy some time
"ZoneID": so she can return with reinforcements."

"InternalName": but was broken to bits because of this."

"A researcher and his apprentice are experimenting with an amulet that protects the wearer from wamasu lightning."

"Sylvian Herius's troops have written petitions
"InternalName": asking the gods' intervention on the rebel side."

"Journal": "Alamar has lost several bottles of wine while on a winery tour. He hired me to find and collect them."

"I met a strange old Wood Elf outside the ancient ruin known as Thormar. She's invited me to a party she calls \"the greatest in all the worlds.\""

"Journal": "Merchants from House Hlaalu are worried about their leader

"Journal": "<<1>> wants my help to prank her Subtle Knife rival

"Journal": "<<1>> believes the Wood Orc clan of Dra'bul

"Journal": "I used the key to search the House Dres farmhouses outside Mournhold. I found a suspicious-looking trap door hidden under a rug. Naryu thinks we'll discover a connection to the Maulborn down there."
"The Mane has released Dro-m'athra spirits on Fort Grimwatch! Twins <<1>> and <<2>>
"Zone": lead the fight against the creatures."

Zahari has learned that weapons imbued with enchantments powered by Daedric souls are particularly powerful against Dragons. I need to collect these souls to help fight back against the Dragon threat."

"I've worked with the Lunar Champion Shazah to seal up corruption wells inside of Fort Grimwatch. Now I've met up with her sister Khali to explore an unearthed Khajiiti temple."

"In the wake of a Dro-m'Athra attack

"Journal": "I accepted one of the Dark Brotherhood's murder-for-hire contracts

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Glademist

"InternalName": as Colovian forces attempt to take an Ayleid ruin from Dominion soldiers."

"Journal": "<<1>> and his brother

"Journal": "The Bloody Hand Goblins have stolen Cropsford's seeds

"A drunk named Shazeem seems to have lost his memory. He offered to sell me a trained monkey
"InternalName": claiming it can find buried treasure."

"Journal": "Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe
"Zone": wants me to go to Bok-Xul and accomplish the task he set before me."

"Journal": "In a cave full of plunder
"InternalName": I found a dead man clutching a note to his sister. Though the bracelet accompanying the note has little monetary value
"Zone": his sister may be glad to have it back."

"Journal": "<<1>> is willing to give me some property if I help resolve a personal matter."
"Ufgra gra-Gum says that undead creatures infest the ruins of Culotte to the southwest of Cropsford."
"Fists of Thalmor were attacked by strange creatures in <<1>>. While many were slain

"InternalName": the ingredients-and Mindileth-can be found in Grahtwood."

"Journal": "Captain Naros
"Zone": is investigating a rash of disappearances near Molag Mar. I agreed to assist her in getting to the root of the cause."

"Journal": "Bloody Hand skirmishers are lurking on the outskirts of town. Ufgra is very worried about them."
"The Bloodthorn Cult recently attacked Stonetooth Fortress. The Orcs repelled the attack but something was stolen."
"I found the journal of a young man named Vareldur in the mine called Del's Claim. He died trying to stop the Heritance from killing the miners there."
"A Dark Elf named Drelyth Hleran requested my aid in finding his family's lost grave site. He believes the Ashlanders camped near Ald'ruhn might know more about the lost tomb
"InternalName": but the tribes only share their secrets with those who earn their respect."

"Journal": "A tailor tried to take a shortcut through Cambray Pass and was attacked by a pack of wild wolves. He lost the tools of his trade as he fled. He asked me to retrieve his possessions and meet him at the northern end of the pass."

"I found a message within Cryptwatch Fort indicating that the Red Rooks are worried the Bloodthorn cult will turn against them. The note also contains recipes for salves and potions to combat the Bloodthorns' festering magic."
"Though I've gathered all the tablets
"InternalName": the Xinchei-Konu remains powerless. Jekka-Wass Vozei wishes to perform a ritual to help the monument regain its magical properties
"Zone": but needs the help of his mentor Nisswo Paraxeeh to do so."

"Journal": "Iron Orcs
"Zone": have started abducting travelers near the Valley of Scars. I encountered a caravan master who survived an attack
"ZoneID": though a number of his guards were dragged off by the Orcs."

"Journal": "The lunar priests at the Do'Krin Monastery have been attacked by the Stonefire cult. The survivors fear the cultists mean to steal a sacred relic: The Golden Claw."
"I found the body of a Khajiiti woman on the terrace of Do'Krin Monastery. She was still clutching a letter and a small offering to the Bright Moons."
"Battlereeve Alduril would like me to assist her in her assault on Tempest Island."

"Zone": gave me a challenge to complete in Claw's Strike

"InternalName": in an attempt to bring them into Coldharbour: one Dunmer
"ZoneID": and one Orc. The Dunmer <<1>> has a plan to help herself and the other village leaders escape."

"Journal": "An undead army surges through Driladan Pass and assaults Marbruk on the command of the Shade of Prince Naemon."

"<<1>> is under siege
"InternalName": but the commander at the gate doesn't seem worried."

"The farmers of Root-Whisper Village are in need of a rare mushroom that goes in Blight Bog Sump. I'll need to make my way past the dangerous creatures that lurk there in order to gather this plant."
"The Prophet and I are seeking a way to rescue Sai Sahan
"InternalName": the Redguard who hid away the Amulet of Kings."

"Journal": "<<1>> lost his lute in a riddle game with <<2>>."
"In the depths of <<1>> I came across the corpse of <<2>>
"InternalName": cooked in his armor by a beast that dwells there."

"<<1>> needs special mushrooms found only in <<2>> to help the wounded."
"Many of Bruma's citizens are lost or missing in the ruins."

"A woman claiming to be the leader of the Scaled Court requested my help. This Regent Cassipia wants me to help her stop the Scaled Court's process for creating a new type of creature for the Serpent's growing army-the mantikora."
"I've found a scared bandit trying to hide in Portdun Watch. He wants me to take a token to his brother
"InternalName": though he was too frightened to tell me much more."

"Journal": "<<1>> needs his restoration scrolls charged."
"<<1>> challenged me to learn more about the enemy so I can appreciate the dangers the folk of Bruma face."
"After the death of Prince Naemon
"InternalName": Vicereeve Pelidil assumed leadership of the Veiled Heritance and stole the Staff of Magnus. Razum-dar has tracked him to somewhere in the area of Woodhearth."

"Journal": "<<1>> believes a Shadowed Path Magister is leading Bruma's intruders."
"Imperial battlemage and former Grand Chancellor of the Empire
"Zone": requested my assistance with an important matter that could lead to the end of the Three Banners War."

"Journal": "Evidence suggests that Vicereeve Pelidil and the Veiled Heritance are planning to attack the city of Woodhearth."
"<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in Stormhaven."
"<<1>> asked me to search the manor for hidden Dremora portals."
"The Veiled Heritants plan to harm the Wilderking. If I enter Aranias' past through Maruin's story

"<<1>> of the Fighters Guild learned of Worm Cult activity in the Rift."
"Shifty Tom
"Zone": wants to give up the pirate's life. He plans to leave Blackheart Haven
column8: but wants me to help him steal two magical relics from the Captain

"To learn why the Wood Elves in this part of the Valenwood are opposed to the Dominion and to convince them to change their mind
"InternalName": I must negotiate with the Wilderking."

"Zone": gave me a challenge to complete in Norvulk Ruins

"InternalName": sworn to imprison the spirit of High Kinlord Rilis

"ZoneID": but will require fighting the Keepers directly."

"Journal": "This tower is a lightless oubliette
"InternalName": a prison of darkness that binds King Laloriaran Dynar

"I met a Khajiit named Zhasim who was raised as part of an Orc clan. An old pack within the ancient ruins inside Bonerock Cavern contained a Khajiit medallion. Could it be a clue to Zhasim's origin?"
"The Maormer seek to prevent the Dominion from establishing themselves on <<1>>. They've launched a full-scale attack on <<2>>."
"I met a man named Armin in the bottom of Divad's Chagrin mine. After seven years searching
"InternalName": he found his ancestors remains and wants to send word to his wife that he will soon return home."

"Journal": "I met Gadris the Dark Elf and Zur the Khajiit. These two mages share a single body
"InternalName": as their souls were melded at this Vile Laboratory when they arrived in Coldharbour. This soul-meld has weakened them. If they remain combined
