"InternalName": but an old treaty with the Maormer prevents this."

"Zone": believes he was murdered. She suspects <<3>>
column8: conspired to kill him. <<1>> is convinced <<3>> secretly worships Boethiah

"Journal": "A powerful mage named <<1>> went missing in the Temple of the Mourning Springs. I agreed to help his apprentice <<2>> search the temple for signs of her master."
"I came across a magical recording of Vanus Galerion. The message says that the mage decided to enter the Black Forge on his own. He plans to reach the Great Shackle and destroy it
"InternalName": thus completing our mission in Coldharbour."

"Journal": "I found a broken cart with a list of items that were supposed to be delivered to Lorene Menillet of Cropsford."
"I found a bundle of damaged gifts meant for <<1>> who lives in <<2>>."
"Rasha has asked me to deliver a small pouch of sand to an old friend."

"ZoneID": an old relic of Malacath. She wants me to recover it before they can."

"Journal": "I met a mage named <<1>> in Darkshade Caverns. She has asked for help investigating the Dwemer ruins beneath the mines."
"Some of the mages who helped open the initial portal to Coldharbour were captured when they arrived. Now they're prisoners in the Daedric Court of Contempt
"InternalName": awaiting the verdict of Judge Xiven in the Hall of Judgment."

"Journal": "Thizzrini Arena is host to numerous arena games in a sprawling complex outside of Dune. To compete in the games
"InternalName": I must speak with the three Division Champions and earn the proper credentials."

"Journal": "I am competing in the Swordmaster Division of Thizzrini Arena. I must rise through the ranks of contenders before I can battle Zara

"Zone": sent his thugs to kill me and failed. His business partner
column8: has grown tired of his slave-trading operation and wants me to eliminate him."

"Journal": "I've found a note from a Dwemer researcher's journal named Tharayya. She appears to have been searching for an ancient artifact referred to as the \"Guardian's Eye.\""
"<<1>> has taken to hunting Daedra for sport and profit. She's asked for my help in exchange for a cut of the earnings."
"I found a notebook full of observations about the Ayleid wells around Cyrodiil. The book's owner may want it back."
"Lady Laurent is displeased with her butler
"Zone": for leading the Elves to Salas En. To get back in her good favor
"ZoneID": he's asked me to help him by gathering Laurent's tools from among the ruins."

"Journal": "A suspicious woman asked me to relay a message to <<1>> in Bruma."
"I found a note in a smuggler camp. A young Khajiit was captured and taken to <<1>> by the <<m:2>>."
"Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore beyond the portal in Veteran City of Ash in Greenshade."
"I found a small silver flute in a crate. An inscription on the flute reads
"InternalName": \"Halion of Chorrol.\" There might be a reward for the flute's return."

"Journal": "I'm now partcipating in Lizard Racing
"InternalName": where I place bets on which lizard finishes the race first."

"Journal": "I'm now participating in Spikeball
"InternalName": a foot race where I can throw a Spikeball to stun opponents."

"Journal": "I was tipped off about rare gems stashed in the Glittering Grotto. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved
"InternalName": so I should act quickly on this lead."

"Journal": "I'm now betting on the Troll Arena
"InternalName": where I place bets on which Troll wins the fight."

"Journal": "<<1>> at the <<2>> asked me to deliver a letter to his cousin Asvorn in <<3>>."
"The chief of the Ash'abah and many of the tribe's warriors have been poisoned
"InternalName": most likely by the Withered Hand. I agreed to help Talia at-Marimah gather ingredients for an antidote."

"Journal": "There's a crisis at <<1>>. Something is wrong with their Great Tree
"InternalName": and the locals believe it has something to do with the tree's roots
"Zone": which can be accessed from a cave below it."

"Journal": "Someone named Jena is being threatened. She apparently lives in Cheydinhal."
"I met <<1>> fishing in the cold waters of northern Cyrodiil. She asked if I could bring some of her catch to her friend <<2>> in <<3>>."
"Sea Elves have entered Serpent's Grotto
"InternalName": and one of the Maormer mages has broken the seals that bound a massive sea serpent here for centuries."

"Journal": "<<1>> needs herbs delivered to <<2>> in <<3>>."
"On his deathbed
"InternalName": the chief of the Ash'abah says he has foreseen that I must join the tribe and defeat the Withered Hand. I must participate in an initiation ritual to become an Ash'abah."

"Journal": "The Eye of the Queen
"Zone": wants my help to uncover corruption in the little town of Pa'alat. She suspects a former Eye of the Queen has gone rogue."

"Journal": "The Shade of Prince Naemon has seized control of Hectahame where he is corrupting the Heart of the Valenwood. I must assist Queen Ayrenn and Indaenir in defeating him."
"A merchant in the Shrouded Vale reports seeing a village that has mysteriously and suddenly appeared in a nearby cave."
"The army has been gathered and the time has come to take the battle to Molag Bal! But to reach the planar vortex at the heart of the Dark Lord's inner sanctum
"InternalName": we have to cross the well-defended Chasm."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Blacksmith goods to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've entered Cyrodiil
"InternalName": eager to help the Dominion win the war."

"Journal": "The merchant lord <<1>> claims to have found <<2>>'s dowry
"InternalName": and for his trouble she has agreed to marry him. <<3>> suspects <<4>>
"Zone": the treacherous former guildmaster of the Thieves Guild
"ZoneID": is behind it all. She wants him to pay for his betrayal."

"Journal": "I've reached the siege range. Zan advised me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Firamo and Miniel to learn more about the weapons."
"Lunar Priestess Kauzanabi-jo has indicated I should make for the temple of Moonmont. The Champions
"InternalName": the new candidates for the Mane

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Enchanter glyphs to an interested organization."

"Journal": "The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to help the people of Arenthia. Apparently Mane Akkhuz-ri is somewhere amid the Colovian invaders of the city."
"I traveled to the city of Rawl'kha
"InternalName": where I'm to help the Lunar Champions begin their spiritual journey."

"Journal": "I saved Dune from the plots of Javad Tharn. Now I must aid the Lunar Champion as she walks the Two Moons Path
"InternalName": a mystical Khajiit ritual used to annoint a new Mane."

"Journal": "Aurorelle Varin says there is much more for me to learn about the war in Cyrodiil."

"I've been asked by a moon priestess named Felari to help with a project that could help firm up relations between the Khajiit and Wood Elves. They are working to return home relics and bones from ancient battle sites."
"The Mages Guild has launched an expedition into Selene's Web to seek out and study an ancient forest spirit rumored to live here."
"Queen Ayrenn must deal with the aftermath of her brother's betrayal and settle matters in Grahtwood. In the meantime
"InternalName": she asked me to travel to Marbruk
"ZoneID": and secure the Staff of Magnus from its vault."

"Journal": "The Wood Elf brewing town of Willowgrove is trying to expand their beehives. They've hired help to clear the forest. This help appears to have suffered some difficulties."
"<<1>> runs a finder's business and uses the Thieves Guild to track down his quarries. Helping him will surely reflect well on your skill as a thief
"Pelidil's plans to lead the Maormer in attack against Valenwood have been exposed and Treethane Fariel suggests I go to Seaside Sanctuary to try to repel the Maormer invasion."
"I met a Dark Elf named Dralnas who claims that Dremora have taken his soul to feed to something he calls the Anguish Gem."
"The mine called Kuna's Delve has been assaulted by a pack of bloodthirsty trolls."
"Aranias and Andur were sent by the Veiled Heritance to kill the Wilderking. They are now forcing their way through Greenheart towards the Wilderking's throne."
"I've arrived at Leki's Blade
"InternalName": a school of swordsmanship in the sands of Alik'r."

"Journal": "I met a Soul Shriven named Fatahala. She claims that this Manor of Revelry isn't what it appears to be. Furthermore
"InternalName": she wants me to help Stibbons
"Zone": who she tells me is in mortal danger here."

"Journal": "I have been welcomed into the bizarre realm of the Daedric Demiprince Fa-Nuit-Hen. In order to test my mettle and demonstrate my skills
"InternalName": I've agreed to enter the Maelstrom Arena
"Zone": where deadly challenges created by Fa-Nuit-Hen's Barons await me."

"Journal": "The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to make for the temple in Rawl'kha. I need to aid the Lunar Champions in their journey."
"I accepted a bounty to investigate unnatural phenomena preventing the excavation of Tribune's Folly."
"The bandits at Sep's Spine have canceled hostilities for sake of the boss's daughter's wedding."
"A courier came to me with an urgent request to go help Prince Azah fight in the small town of Tava's Blessing and to send the Scholar's apprentice
"Abnur Tharn seeks an audience with me away from the Harborage. I should see what he wants."
"<<1>> is a town in Bangkorai fabled to have the power to cure any disease. <<2>> and his husband Draven seek whatever cure the village offers
"InternalName": though they don't know what the cost may be."

"Journal": "Mighty Mordra
"Zone": has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted."

"Journal": "I found an odd
"InternalName": glowing handaxe in a pack at the bottom of Gurzag's Mine. A note of sale indicated a Bosmer named Forthor sold it to the Orcs. He's part of the Marbruk Mages Guild."

"Journal": "Thonoras and his wife
"Zone": were captured and tortured by Wood Orcs. Pariel begged Hircine to save them
"ZoneID": and Hircine \"changed her.\" After helping her husband escape
column8: Pariel disappeared into a cave beneath the Falinesti Spring Site."

"Journal": "I found a talking skull named <<1>> near <<Ac:2>>. He wants me to piece him together so he can help thwart Worm Cultists in the area."

"A group of Orc artisans was heading to the new city of Orsinium when they were attacked by members of the Trinimac cult known as the Vosh Rakh and taken prisoner in the ruins of Paragon's Remembrance."
"I ran into a very hung-over mage in Rawl'kha. He had too much to drink
"Zone": and now fears he'll never gain an apprenticeship to Telenger the Artificer."

"Journal": "Tappo's journal details his victims. He kept a keepsake from each."
"Whisper Grove has been turned to a City of Ash by the forces of Mehrunes Dagon. If I don't intervene
"InternalName": the remaining Bosmer will be slaughtered."

"Journal": "I convinced the leaders of the three alliances to meet to discuss a plan to attack Molag Bal's realm of Coldharbour. The meeting takes place on the historic island of Stirk. Hopefully

"Zone": informed me of bandits who kidnapped his daughter <<3>>. He asked me to bring her home safely."

"Journal": "A small group of Wood Elves entered the Falinesti Spring Site
"InternalName": which has been taken over by Wood Orcs. When they petitioned the Wood Orcs to leave
"Zone": they were taken prisoner. Egannor managed to escape
"ZoneID": but his friends are still in the camp."

"Journal": "A stone being named Sumiril carries a book that contains a story about how he came to be."
"The eccentric artificer and dungeon-delver
"Zone": needs more data for his experiments. He's certain that the information he requires can be found in a Dwarven ruin called Zthenganaz."

"Journal": "I met a Khajiit called Cold-Eyes who is looking to collect a debt. He'll give me a cut if I help him."
"A shady character told me I was needed at the city of Arenthia. This Orthoron said someone of my prowess would come in handy."
"A strange priest at an old Khajiiti ruin told me that my path is laid out before him. He suggests I go to the city of Rawl'kha to learn more."
"I found a journal that belonged to a monk of the Lunar faith named Yenadar. The journal mentions that he has a sister named Kala in S'ren-ja. I should return the journal to her."
"I agreed to gather Red Mountain Ash for <<1>>
"InternalName": so he can make Nirnroot wine."

"Journal": "Master Pellingare
column8: have come to the sewers looking for him after he was last seen heading into the undercity tunnels."

"Journal": "The Dragonstar Caravan Company's job broker
"Zone": has tasked me with traveling to Argent Mine to slay werewolves. A wealthy client will pay handsomely for their skins."

"Journal": "I discovered the body of one of the Fighters Guild soldiers in Mal Sorra's Tomb. She started writing a note to her cousin
"Nature itself has turned against the Bosmer village of Karthdar and its citizens are desperate to restore peace."
"After defeating the Maormer assault on Khenarthi's Roost
"InternalName": Razum-dar has asked me to report to <<1>> in the Auridon city of Vulkhel Guard."

"Journal": "I've been given a letter to deliver to Queen Ayrenn to bring her up to speed on the events that have occurred and inform her of our victory over Vicereeve Pelidil."
"My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City."
"A Bosmer named Adamir
"Zone": are attempting to animate an assemblage of rodent parts."

"Journal": "Radreth
"InternalName": a new member of the hunting company the Hounds
"Zone": asked for my help in hunting a giant wasp."

"Journal": "I've been summoned back to the Harborage in preparation for our battle against Molag Bal."
"I've discovered an order of hunters called Brackenleaf's Briars. They protect a tree they say was planted by Y'ffre at the creation of the world."
"While exploring the Tribulation Crypt
"InternalName": I encountered a ghost that beckoned me deeper into the tomb. The ghost led me to an ancient sword engraved with the following message: \"Marcelle Stenric of Shornhelm."

"Journal": "Varen Aquilarios and Abnur Tharn have found the location of Sai Sahan within the Halls of Torment. I need to venture into these halls and save the final
"Varen Aquilarios asked me to accompany Sai Sahan on a trip back to his ancestral home. An old friend
"Zone": may have knowledge of how to sneak into Sancre Tor."

"Journal": "I met a Mages Guild novice named Anenya just inside the Erokii Ruins. She was sent here on an assignment to recover a relic called the Tear of Anurraame
"InternalName": but she can't carry it out. I agreed to recover the relic and bring it back to Shornhelm."

"Journal": "The Rain Catcher Fields
"InternalName": a sandy expanse of johads gathering water in large pools
"Zone": has recently been overrun by beetles from the desert."

"Journal": "Undead soldiers have been haunting Traitor's Tor ever since the end of Ranser's War
"InternalName": but no one's ever been able to find out why."

"Journal": "I have found the notes of a mage named Mercano from Woodhearth in the depths of an Ayleid ruin where the Veiled Heritants were raising undead."
"The time has come to confront Molag Bal and reclaim my soul."
"I discovered the remains of a mage outside a cave in Shademist Moors. While there are no shortage of victims around here
"InternalName": the presence of the Mages Guild urges me to investigate what might have happened to the rest of them."

"Journal": "The Shade of Prince Naemon is spreading corruption across Greenshade. I must help Indaenir cleanse the corruption."

"The Torog's Spite Bandits are dedicated to profit and vengeance from targeting families descended from those who sacked Orsinium. An Orc historian named Maaga wants to record the bandits' deeds but needs to know which Orc clan deserves credit."
"Before losing Aranias' memories
"InternalName": the Wilderqueen told me that she knew about the Veiled Heritance plot to steal the Staff of Magnus. She suggested I go to the city of Woodhearth."

"Journal": "Captain Jimila has been suffering under the oppressive dock fees in Anvil. She asked for my help in stealing the dock master's private stash to pay off her debts."
"I met a Bosmer Adventurer named Gluineth locked in a cell in Troll's Toothpick. I've agreed to spring her from the cell and escort her out of the cave."
"I found a Knight of St. Pelin in the Crypt of the Exiles who died while on an important quest. She sought to recover a sacred Redguard artifact
"InternalName": the Memory Stone of Makela Leki
"Zone": and return it to a Redguard scholar."

"Journal": "Sai Sahan has recovered from his experiences in the the Halls of Torment and is ready to guide me to the Amulet of Kings. He hid the artifact in Sancre Tor
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a mission to help capture farms
"Zone": and mines for the Dominion. Conquering any nine of these resources will complete my mission."

"Journal": "I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Arkas at the Southern Morrowind gate."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Arkas at the Southern Morrowind gate."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Ikran at the Northern High Rock gate in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil."
"I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Ikran at the Northern High Rock gate."
"The princess of Evermore is being cared for in the Viridian Woods
"<<1>>'s husband
"Zone": went missing after going on tour through <<2>>. I agreed to help track him down."

"InternalName": one of the legendary resting places of the Walking City of Falinesti
"Zone": is buzzing with activity. It seems <<2>> has begun an excavation."

"Journal": "Lady Clarisse Laurent is on the trail of the Emerald Chalice
"InternalName": a relic stolen from the Mages Guild by the exiled Nord mage
"Zone": Malofar. She tracked him here to Breagha-Fin."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars."
"The Reachmen threat has been averted
"InternalName": but Evermore is still in danger
"Zone": and Queen Arzhela needs my help."

"Journal": "On approaching <<1>>
"Zone": a Khajiit in trouble with the local authorities."

"Journal": "The Llodos plague is ravaging the Deshaan countryside. I met someone from a town known as the Serk. He's on his way to warn people about the plague."
"I found a strange glowing amulet on a corpse in the woods."
"<<1>> has heard rumblings of discontent in <<2>>
"InternalName": the Aldmeri Dominion's capital. She wants me to travel ahead of her and assess the situation."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades."
"Reachmen attacked Northglen. They must be stopped before they can attack the city of Evermore."
"Imperials have been raiding Martyr's Crossing
"InternalName": and the Knights of Saint Pelin have wound up having to depend on the help of Baandari merchants for assistance."

"Journal": "A bloody conflict has erupted between the noble houses of Rivenspire and High King Emeric has asked me to go there on his authority and attempt to restore order."
"According to Jee-Lar
"InternalName": poison-sniffing skinks can provide some much-needed security in the wilds of Murkmire. He needs me to acquire one of these valuable lizards in Alik'r."

"Journal": "Scholar <<1>> and his guide
"InternalName": <<2>> became separated in the Sunken Road."

"Journal": "Imperial forces have taken control of Bangkorai Garrison
"InternalName": the strategic keep that divides northern and southern Bangkorai. King Emeric and the Lion Guard have come to aid Queen Arzhela and the Knights of Saint Pelin in reconquering the garrison."

"Journal": "Little Leaf has asked me to find her friend
"Zone": in Dragonstar. She claims that the two of them are working from the inside to stop the Scaled Court."

"Journal": "The ruins of the ancient Wood Elf village of Gil-Var-Delle is under the corrupting influence of Molag Bal. The Worm Cult is active here
"InternalName": and my help is needed to put an end to their schemes."

"Journal": "<<1>> is distraught. Her adorable pet
"ZoneID": and she's afraid that the little creature is lost."

"Journal": "The riddles I uncovered with Xukas and Jaxsik-Orrn pointed us to a mysterious locale known as the Swallowed Grove. According to Famia
"InternalName": I will have to undertake a dream-wallow vision to learn the truth of the Remnant of Argon."

"Journal": "Hallin's Stand is ready to take back their town from the Imperial's Seventh Legion."
"InternalName": "BK HS The Shifting Sands of Fa"

"Journal": "I met <<1>> and <<2>> at their camp along the roadside. They're fleeing for their lives from their ransacked farmstead."
"According to a note I discovered in Coldperch Cavern
"InternalName": a hagraven named Kraala uses a totem to transform people into birds."

"Journal": "Adusa has further need of my help. She's learned of another plot
"InternalName": an assassin contracted by allies of House Montclair."

"Journal": "Adusa has discovered that the Montclairs have assembled a list of targets they have marked for elimination."
"I returned to find Adusa and Castle Ravenwatch under attack. The list of targets puts Adusa right at the top."
"I found a pack with a romantic poem and frog totem in the middle of the swamp. If I return these items to their rightful owner
"<<1>> has asked me to find her husband Ignobert
"InternalName": who went missing after a vampire attack."

"Journal": "Now that the threat to Rivenspire has been dealt with
"InternalName": there's still the matter of crowning a true ruler for the region."

"Journal": "Countess Tamrith has sent a priest to sanctify her dead soldiers at Camp Tamrith. Those particularly devoted to the Light of Arkay have a profound fear of turning into undead creatures."
"I found a notice calling for warriors to join a Death-Hunt."
"Fallen Grotto is under the control of <<1>> and his Reachmen."
"<<1>> has lost track of her husband and her dog. I've offered to help her look for both of them."
"All is not well in <<1>>. The Khajiit lack an embassy
"InternalName": which is the cause of tensions in the capital city of the Aldmeri Dominion."

"Journal": "I discovered a research journal kept by an Orc named Grularz in Crestshade Mine. She was apparently studying the trolls until they decided to kill her. The journal referred to a brother named Gothurg in Shornhelm."
"Maj al-Ragath has challenged me to explore the ruins beneath Grahtwood
"Adusa fears that Montclair agents still operate out of Shornhelm. She wants me to follow a courier in hopes the courier will lead me to the Montclair informer."
"<<1>> is concerned for her friend <<2>>. He recently entered a cave full of deadly spiders and hasn't been seen since."
"Jowan and Mayla want to give their family a proper burial. They asked me to accompany them."
"I met an old scholar near the Ayleid ruins who came to power a crystal for his research
"InternalName": but found the ruins swarming with Worm Cultists."

"Journal": "I found a journal that belonged to a thief called Nedras the Sly. He apparently turned to crime in order to support his ailing sister in Northpoint."
"I found a journal on the body of Klaandor Axe-Bearer. It details his transformation into a vampire. Seems like he was looking for someone to kill him."
"I found a journal that belonged to a monk of the lunar faith named Yenadar. The journal mentions that he has a sister named <<1>> in S'ren-ja. I should return the journal to her."

"Lleraya Montclair and her forces have taken control of Northpoint. They've sealed the gates and locked out the legitimate city guards. But Baron Dorell has a plan to liberate Northpoint. It just requires a small group willing to infiltrate the city."
"After their defeat at Bangkorai Garrison
"Zone": and King Emeric believes they will make their last stand here at the ancient temple known as the Hall of Heroes."

"Journal": "Imperial Magus-General Septima Tharn captured King Emeric and took him into the Chamber of Passage. It's apparently a gateway to the plane known as the Far Shores
"InternalName": where Redguards go in the afterlife."

"Journal": "I met Nicolene in the Dead Wolf Inn in Shornhelm. She and Captain Kaleen are here looking for one of King Fahara'jad's former spies
"InternalName": Naruk. Naruk has turned against the Daggerfall Covenant and is now inciting war

"Journal": "I found a wanted poster offering a reward for the head of an Orc called Sgolag."
"A Daedra has taken over Nilata Ruins. Having possessed a farmer's wife
"InternalName": the Daedra is luring travelers into her lair-likely to their doom."

"Journal": "Something has been luring Imperial soldiers into the ruins. Many have been captured by the giant spiders lurking there."

"We found a way to sneak into the sealed city of Northpoint-a tunnel used by smugglers and black marketeers. Now we need to head inside and find a way to free the city from Lleraya Montclair's grasp."
"While traveling in <<1>>
"InternalName": I found a shrine dedicated to the animals of the Valenwood. <<2>> said the shrine was created by <<3>>'s Briars

"Journal": "I met a priest of Y'ffre who seeks to heal the scarred ruin of Gil-Var-Delle by mixing blessed water into the falls that feed into the river of the vale. She asked me to help her in her task."
"<<1>>'s Carnival came from the Summerset Isle to spread High Elf culture. Unfortunately
"InternalName": they've suffered numerous setbacks in performing for the Wood Elves of <<2>>."

"Journal": "Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Vaults of Madness
"InternalName": a dark labyrinth at the heart of Coldharbour."

"Journal": "High King Emeric wants to liberate southern Bangkorai from Imperial control. He believes the key to that is tracking down Imperial Magus General Septima Tharn."
"Loremaster Celarus and the Psijic scryers have finally discovered the four remaining pieces of the Staff of Towers. I must travel to remote locations to find and recover these artifacts."
"<<1>> asked me to search the ruins for texts from other scholars who may have previously studied here."
"Llotha asked me to help her unlock a lockbox by solving an old mystery about the Blacklight Raiders. The password to the lock is a combination of the Raiders' names and professions."
"I found a journal in a bandit camp. It detailed the murder of an Orc chieftan's two wives. It also mentioned a third wife named <<1>> who lives in a place called Barkbite."
"I accepted a mission to help capture farms
"Zone": and mines for the Covenant. Conquering any nine of these resources will complete my mission."
seeks to rally others to his banner by acquiring Captain Helenus's Helm from the Seventh Legion <<3>> who devastated his Orcish brethren."

"Journal": "As <<1>> and a group of refugees traveled through southern Bangkorai
"InternalName": they were attacked by Imperials. Several of them lost priceless heirlooms."

"Journal": "The Wyress Freyda warned me away from Jackdaw Cove as dark forces are at work in northern Bangkorai."
"A group of soldiers from Bangkorai Garrison lead by Sir Dubroc went out in search of the Reachman leader in Jackdaw Cove."
"<<1>> has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted."
"Cadwell has turned the Harborage into his new home-for the time being
and Be Merry"
"Zone": "I found a keg containing wine with magical properties."

"Journal": "Something strange is happening inside Shroud Hearth Barrow that is frightening the villagers of Ivarstead."
"I found an abandoned campfire at the entrance to <<1>>. I should figure out what happened to the campers."
"The Dominion's lifeline to Malabal Tor is under siege. If I want to assist in the defense of <<1>>
"InternalName": I should speak with <<2>> near the gate to <<3>>."

"Journal": "A Pact soldier and his brother were captured by bandits after being caught spying. They were investigating the cult-like activity of the bandits."
"The Ring of Daggers has tracked down a war criminal named Gerard Althen
"InternalName": who once served as King Ranser's spymaster. He's hiding somewhere in Sanguine Barrows and I've agreed to find him and bring him out."

"Journal": "<<1>> overheard Dominion soldiers brag of capturing <<Ac:2>>
"InternalName": where Argonian children in <<3>> are born."

"Journal": "At Paragon's Remembrance
"InternalName": I learned that the Vosh Rakh plan to harm Chief Bazrag and High Priestess Solgra before they attack the chiefs at the king's moot in Orsinium. I need to find a way to stop them."

"Journal": "I managed to drive the bandits from Fell's Run
"Captain Thayer is having a difficult time recruiting new soldiers for the Shornhelm Guard. She asked me to help convince a man in the stocks to enlist."
"Captain Thayer thinks her last prospect will pose the greatest challenge of all. His name is Julien Rissiel and he's reluctant to enlist because he's in love."
"Captain Thayer has asked me to recruit a woman named Shuga into the Shornhelm Guard. Thayer suspects Shuga is actually a bandit who doesn't have much respect for the guard."
"We put an end to Reezal-Jul and Lleraya. Now we need to deal with Baron Montclair. But to reach Montclair in his citadel atop the Doomcrag
"InternalName": we first need to find a way through the Shrouded Pass."

"Journal": "As part of the South Winds Festival
"InternalName": there is a mounted race being proctored by the priests of Kynareth. Participants of the derby will be rewarded with a blessing of good health if they can prove themselves worthy by beating a timed trial."

"Journal": "A Herald has come with tales of a dire threat in the distant land of Craglorn."
"Lieutenant Slonn led a team of scholars to Pinepeak Caverns to awaken the spirit of Hakra
"InternalName": one of the five hundred companions

"Journal": "I found a soldier outside a spider cave in Stonefalls. She's suffering from a spider bite she received while trying to search the Hollow."
"A High Elf named Caalorne was ambushed by a group of Argonians on the road to Kragenmoor. They stole a number of potions from him
"I met a soldier at Ash Mountain who said the defense of Davon's Watch could use some help."
"A soldier at Fort Virak told me the Pact military is focusing their efforts at the land coral maze known as Vivec's Antlers."
"A Pact officer at Vivec's Antlers suggested I assist the generals at Ash Mountain."

"The skinned bodies of Argonians are being placed on display around Murkmire by a killer dubbed \"the Skin Taker.\" I have been asked to help find this killer before anyone else falls victim to their grisly methods."
"Captain Ronag at Shinji's Scarp asked me to deliver a dispatch to Clan Murtag soldiers near the at-Tura estate."
"I ran into Blademaster Qariar in Northpoint's back alleys. He's hunting down the remaining vampires that were working with Lady Lleraya Montclair."
"A guardswoman in Skywatch has asked me to deliver a sealed message scroll to Vulkhel Guard for her."
"Something about the way the book was placed in front of the statue makes it appear to be an offering."
"I found a grave-stake lying next to a note indicating that it was stolen. I should find out who to return the grave-stake to."
"I met Ibrula
"InternalName": a friend of the Star-Gazers who is trying to get into a ruined temple called the Seeker's Archive. She hopes to discover information inside that will help defeat the Celestials."

"Journal": "An aging Bosmer named Hartmin brought his dying husband to a grove near Greenheart where they share memories from their youth."
"I found the ruins of a city called Shada's Tear in the middle of the Craglorn desert. A mercenary told me that some researchers from Belkarth went into the ruins
"InternalName": but that strange things started happening when they did."

"Journal": "Outside the school of blades called Rahni'Za
"InternalName": I encountered an intiate of the school who told me that the Sword-Disciples have been turned into thralls by a traitor. This betrayer now hides in the cavern at the end of the school's five trials."

"Journal": "People venturing into Hel Ra Citadel have mysteriously vanished
"InternalName": including a group of Undaunted led by Kailstig the Axe. I should enter the Citadel to find out what happened to them."

"Journal": "It seems that Prince Naemon has indeed returned from the dead and now leads an undead army that's pushed its way to the city gates of Marbruk."
"The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to help the Lunar Champions Rid-Thar spoke of. I should seek them out at the fort known as Grimwatch."
"Shazah told me to travel to the city of Rawl'kha. There the next steps can be taken to name a new Mane."
"I've discovered the Aetherian Archive
"InternalName": an enigmatic tower that had previously been sealed. Mighty Mordra and her Undaunted had planned to climb the Archive
"Zone": but her allies are missing. If I choose to
"ZoneID": I could explore it and reach the top before them."

"Journal": "A shipment from Artisans Craftworks in Mournhold never made it to the merchant
"Refugees outside of Elinhir told me that the city has been ransacked by mad mages. They sent me to Minerva Lauzon
"InternalName": who is gathering survivors in the sewers."

"Journal": "A giant object fell from the heavens when the Mage constellation disappeared. Sara Benele is examining the object
"InternalName": which she calls the \"Mage's Staff.\" She believes the staff is unstable and needs my help to fix it."

"Journal": "Hermaeus Mora asked me to bring him unique relics from across Craglorn in exchange for knowledge of the Celestials. Perhaps he'll be interested in this strange writing."
"I found a letter from High-King Emeric offering amnesty to the bandits who reside in the ruins of Watcher's Hold. The <<z:1>> also brought a chest of gold as a sign of the king's good faith."
"Nerien'eth the lich has returned to the Crypt of Hearts to find the ghosts he imprisoned there arrayed against him."
"Hara has decided it's time to do something about the third guardian
"InternalName": the Thief. The Thief has been mysteriously absent except for when she appears to speak to me in private."

"Journal": "<<1>> attempted to enter an Oblivion Gate with a group of Undaunted to save his wife
"InternalName": <<2>>. He failed. I'm to help him get her back-if she still lives."

"Journal": "I encountered a Star-Gazer who told me that two High Elf women inside the Crossroad Tavern claim to be aspects of the Celestial Mage. I should talk to them and investigate their claims."
"Safa al-Satakalaam
"Zone": is at odds with the Scaled Court. Three of her most powerful acolytes have deserted her to worship the Celestial Serpent. She wants me to punish these traitors and deny their power to the Scaled Court."

"Journal": "Iron Orcs
"Zone": have started abducting travelers near the Valley of Scars. I encountered a caravan master who survived an attack
"ZoneID": though a number of his guards were dragged off by the Orcs."

"Journal": "A woman claiming to be the leader of the Scaled Court requested my help. This Regent Cassipia wants me to help her stop the Scaled Court's process for creating a new type of creature for the Serpent's growing army-the mantikora."
"Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars."
"Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights."
"Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades."
"Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades."
"Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers."
"Regent Cassipia has asked me to find her seneschal
"Zone": somewhere along the road through the northeast passage. She wants me to offer my aid to Little Leaf and help her foil another one of the Scaled Court's plans."
"ZoneID": "[OLD] CL A Leaf in the Wind"

"Journal": "Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to delve the Banished Cells beneath Auridon."
"The Celestial Warrior is worried about his champion
"Zone": Titus' memory has begun to break apart. He no longer remembers who he is or his connection to the Warrior. Without his memory
"ZoneID": the Warrior can't send him home."

"Journal": "Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the cavern called Spindleclutch beneath Glenumbra."
"Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the kwama mine called Darkshade Caverns
"Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the tunnels and caverns that lie beneath Wayrest
"Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ruined halls of the Crypt of Hearts. It lies beneath the stones of Rivenspire
"InternalName": a former school for might and magic."

"Journal": "Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the ruins and hallways of Veteran Crypt of Hearts
"Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ruins of Arx Corinium
"InternalName": the old Imperial pile sinking into the marsh of Shadowfen."

"Journal": "If I can prove I know my way around a cooking fire
"InternalName": <<1>> will certify me as a provisioner."

"Journal": "Glirion the Redbeard of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Dwemer tunnels of Volenfell
"InternalName": deep beneath the stones of Bangkorai."

"Journal": "If I can prove I know how to use a needle and thread
"InternalName": <<1>> will certify me as a clothier."

"Journal": "I found a book describing an ancient Nedic hero named Ranev the Coal-Eyed Wanderer and her legendary pilgrimage along \"The Gray Passage.\" According to the text
"InternalName": those who complete the pilgrimage in the allotted time gain the favor of the Stars."

"Journal": "I met <<1>>
"InternalName": a member of a research expedition looking into the Dwarven ruin of Rkindaleft. While exploring the ruin
"Zone": they were attacked by strange creatures. I told her I would look for any survivors."

"Journal": "Several Orc miners in the Graystone Quarry have vanished under mysterious circumstances. A High Elf researcher likely holds the key to unraveling the mystery."
"I met a researcher named <<1>>. He's interested in learning what fundamentally altered the Orcs in <<2>>."

"I met a member of the Silver Dawn werewolf hunters who might possibly be the last surviving member of the group. She barely escaped an attack on their headquarters in the Argent Mine by the werewolves of the Magnar Pack."
"A mortal wound to <<1>> has thrown Shatul clan into crisis."
"The Daedra have occupied the White-Gold Tower
"InternalName": and I have agreed to help Moth Priest Terran Arminus retrieve an Elder Scroll left inside the Tower Library."

"Journal": "High Priestess Solgra sent Eveli to recruit me for some sort of secret mission. It appears to involve a rescue
"InternalName": but she wants to give me the details in person."

"Journal": "The Khajiit's ancient enemy
"Zone": have emerged from the Dark Behind the World and claimed the Temple of Seven Riddles for the Ghost Moon

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Clothier goods to an interested organization."

"Draugr from a nearby barrow harass the Orcs of Gloorot's clan. A legendary hero named Narsis Dren agreed to help them
"InternalName": but he has yet to return from the ancient barrow."

"Journal": "Lady Sovelle
"Zone": was sent to negotiate a trade agreement with the Orcs. But the fleet was blown off course and wrecked on the ice
"ZoneID": and now Lady Sovelle is missing."

"Journal": "Novice hunters from an Orc clan ran into an unusually organized band of Riekrs. Some hunters were captured
"InternalName": while others went to attempt a rescue and never returned. The hunt leader asked me to find the hunters and acquire the Riekr chief's totem."

"Journal": "<<1>> built a cairn for his grandfather Corgrak
"InternalName": but couldn't retrieve Corgrak's helm from <<2>>."

"Journal": "<<1>> wants to restore the long-lost reputation of Orc cuisine
"InternalName": but her assistant is missing. I agreed to help her until he arrives."
"Q5458 In the Name of the King"

"Journal": "King Kurog seems to be in a foul mood
"InternalName": which has affected everyone in the royal court. His shield-wife indicates that tensions at the keep are on the verge of boiling over. I wonder what happened to darken the king's usually boisterous spirits?"

"Journal": "Worm Cultists are digging up skeletons in the Memorial District and raising them as undead thralls. Some of these skeletons appear to be searching for something underground. I've agreed to help the Drake of Blades find out what they're looking for."

"The minions of Molag Bal are rounding up the Imperial City's clergy and mercilessly torturing them. The Drake of Blades has asked for my help in rescuing one of these prisoners-a priest named Egnatius."
"All of the paths into the moot have been sealed except the one through the temple in Orsinium. Chief Bazrag wants me to get to the temple
"Zone": and then reach the moot before Kurog assassinates the clan chiefs."

"Journal": "I met a scout who serves an Imperial resistance fighter named Captain Caudex. The captain
"InternalName": and a small group of legionary loyalists
"Zone": have held a garrison at the heart of the Nobles District for nearly two months."

"Journal": "One of the survivors of the frozen fleet asked me to keep an eye open for a gold pendant he lost. It was meant to be a gift for his betrothed when they are finally reunited."
"The Ebonheart Pact is locked in an epic struggle for control of the Imperial City. The forces of Molag Bal hold the city in an iron grip
"InternalName": but enemy bannermen also vie for power. The Pact needs my help."

"Journal": "<<1>> has a strange plan to spy on the Worm Cult
"InternalName": but he needs help to see it through."

"Journal": "The Aldmeri Dominion is locked in an epic struggle for control of the Imperial City. The forces of Molag Bal hold the city in an iron grip
"InternalName": but enemy bannermen also vie for power. The Dominion needs my help."

"Journal": "A concerned clerk named <<1>> believes there is a grave threat to the well-being of future generations if the Imperial recordkeeping falls to war."
"The perfidious occupants of Watcher's Hold have regrouped. Even now
"InternalName": they stockpile supplies in preparation for more attacks on the people of Wrothgar. Sergeant Oufa has signed a contract to ensure that the situation is dealt with."

"Journal": "My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City."
"The Dragonstar Caravan Company job broker
"Zone": has tasked me with retrieving some mysterious eggs from Coldperch Cavern."

"Journal": "My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City."
"My Alliance needs scouts to secure rally points across the Imperial City."
"A caravan bringing books to Orsinium has been waylaid by ogres. The books have likely been torn to pieces. If I'm to reassemble them for their rightful owner
"InternalName": these creatures will need to be dealt with."

"Journal": "The Worm Cult has established a foothold in Wrothgar and seeks to summon a beast called Zandadunoz the Reborn. The king's servant
"Zone": demands that I disrupt their scheme."

"Journal": "A Khajiit named Birkhu the Bold has stumbled upon a number of dangerous Dwarven mechanisms
"Zone": Nyzchaleft. These machines pose a threat to Wrothgar and must be dealt with."

"Journal": "<<1>> has concerns about an ambitious merchant lord named <<2>>. She wants to learn if his interests overlap with those of the Thieves Guild."
"Rumors abound that the Dark Brotherhood
"Zone": are on the lookout for members worthy to wield their killing blade. This might be why so many innocents have been murdered of late."

"Journal": "To prove myself to the Dark Brotherhood
"InternalName": Speaker Terenus wants me to murder the Imperial noble named Quintus Jarol."

"Journal": "Walks-Softly needs help dealing with a personal and delicate situation that involves an old friend from his past."
"Vampire hunter Mel Adrys has come to Hrota Cave to track down the dangerous vampire lord Zalar-do
"InternalName": who has been preying on the people of Anvil. I promised to help him slay the vampire and rescue the victims she kidnapped."

"Journal": "Razum-dar tracked an Imperial war criminal to the Garlas Agea ruins to make her pay for attacking innocent noncombatants in Bravil. I agreed to help him dispatch this Captain Jena Apinia and recover the items they stole."

"A Khajiit named Bakhum is worried about a family member who has been writing him unsettling letters about the \"Maw of Lorkhaj.\" He has asked me and eleven friends to help escort him to the Temple of Seven Riddles to make sure everything is all right."
"I was tipped off about treasures stashed in The Hideaway. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved
"InternalName": so I should act quickly on this lead."

"Journal": "I was tipped off about treasures stashed in Underground Sepulcher. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved
"InternalName": so I should act quickly on this lead."

"Journal": "I was tipped off about treasures stashed in the Secluded Sewers. I don't have much time to secure the goods before they're moved
"InternalName": so I should act quickly on this lead."

"Journal": "Another note from Velsa. It seems Narahni is in need of assistance."
"Velsa let me in on one of the perks of being a member of the Thieves Guild: Heists. She's sending me to the guild's heist master to get vetted for work."
"<<1>> runs a finder's business and uses the Thieves Guild to track down his quarries. Helping him will surely reflect well on your skill as a thief

"Journal": "Recent lectures in Kvatch by the Grand Sermonizer of Akatosh and her priests paint the Dark Brotherhood as powerless pretenders not to be feared. Astara wants the Grand Sermonizer dealt with-permanently."
"Governor Fortunata of Anvil has taken a contract with the Dark Brotherhood. She's added a special request
"InternalName": however. She wants to meet with the assassin personally before completing the deal."

"Journal": "The Black Hand has decreed that Lyra the Black Dragon must die for her crimes against the Brotherhood. Green-Venom-Tongue has gone to Knightsgrave to perform the task. Astara has asked me to back him up."
"Speaker Terenus wants to cut off the head of the group that has been moving against the Dark Brotherhood-he wants us to kill Artorius
"InternalName": the Primate of Akatosh. He wants the death to happen quickly
"Zone": before the Order of the Hour attacks the Sanctuary."

"Journal": "Cleric Arvina in Anvil has posted a bounty for any group brave enough to enter Hrota Cave and destroy Exulus
"InternalName": a wispmother claiming the cave as her own. He also asked that the pauldrons of his fallen warriors be retrieved."

"Journal": "I accepted a contract to destroy the beast named <<1>>. It's being held captive deep in the ruins of Garlas Agea by the Gold Coast Trading Company. Additionally
"InternalName": the job calls for me to appropriate company ledgers from their operation there."

"Journal": "The arena master has posted an open challenge for warriors brave enough to fight one of the top gladiators to the death in Kvatch Arena."

"InternalName": who are rumored to appear only during the Witches Festival! Legends say these strange beings can be bargained with for power."

"Journal": "The guardian star sign of the Warrior has failed to appear to protect the mortal world from the Serpent. One of the Star-Gazers needs help uncovering what might be happening."
"A Herald has come with tales of a dire threat in the distant land of Craglorn."

"I met a strange Imperial who was being held captive by the Daggerfall Covenant. He believes he knows how to defeat the cursed army of Anka-Ra that has laid siege to Craglorn since the Celestials appeared."
"Refugees outside of Elinhir told me that the city has been ransacked by mad mages. They sent me to Minerva Lauzon
"InternalName": who is gathering survivors in the sewers."

"Journal": "A giant object fell from the heavens when the Mage constellation disappeared. Sara Benele is examining the object
"InternalName": which she calls the \"Mage's Staff.\" She believes the staff is unstable and needs my help to fix it."

"Journal": "A local dispute over a saltrice farm has now gotten to the point where Sulahkeesh
"Zone": must arbitrate for a resolution to be found. I volunteered to ask the former assassin for her help."

"Journal": "Hermaeus Mora asked me to bring him unique relics from across Craglorn in exchange for knowledge of the Celestials. Perhaps he'll be interested in this strange writing."
"I encountered a Star-Gazer who told me that two High Elf women inside the Crossroad Tavern claim to be aspects of the Celestial Mage. I should talk to them and investigate their claims."
"I met an Iron Orc shaman who had been banished by a younger rival. What's more
"ZoneID": seems to be responsible for the Iron Orc and Scaled Court alliance. The old shaman wants me to avenge him."

"Journal": "A Wood Elf named Little Leaf claims she's on a mission to stop the Iron Orcs from building a troll army. She tried to appeal to the Orc leaders
"InternalName": but diplomacy didn't work. Now she wants me to come along and try a more forceful approach."

"Journal": "A devout knight of the Divines discovered that the dead have awakened in the depths of Skyreach Catacombs. If the legend of Virmaril is true
"InternalName": then a powerful Elven necromancer could be the source of the trouble."

"Journal": "Captain Telomure has asked me to destroy a pearl that's been stolen by a member of the Divine Prosecution
"InternalName": Justiciar Avanaire. The pearl is somewhere in Tor-Hame-Khard."

"Journal": "Regent Cassipia has asked me to find her seneschal
"Zone": somewhere along the road through the northeast passage. She wants me to offer my aid to Little Leaf and help her foil another one of the Scaled Court's plans."
"ZoneID": "NCL Q5774 A Leaf in the Wind"

"Journal": "Little Leaf has asked me to find her friend
"Zone": in Dragonstar. She claims that the two of them are working from the inside to stop the Scaled Court."

"Journal": "I found a book describing an ancient Nedic hero named Ranev the Coal-Eyed Wanderer and her legendary pilgrimage along \"The Gray Passage.\" According to the text

"The recently freed Argonian slave
"Zone": seeks to continue her climb through the ranks of House Telvanni. She needs my help to claim the next title."

"Journal": "The Teeth of Sithis
"InternalName": a pair of ancient xanmeer temples
"Zone": has been overtaken by the servants of its heretical
column8: Shuxaltsei. She has taken the custodians of the Teeth captive and is sacrificing them in some profane blood rite."

"Journal": "According to a masked vigilante known as the Scarlet Judge
"InternalName": a corrupt marshal named Hlaren is oppressing the citizens of Suran. I must aid the Judge in rooting out this corruption."

"Journal": "I've been hired to defeat a nix-ox that has been eating mushrooms the wizard Bravosi Felder is attempting to research. I'm also required to collect samples of the mushrooms while in the area."
"Dradeiva
"Zone": seeks to prove that the Imperial Ninth Legion disappeared in the Tsofeer Caverns. She hopes to show that her ancestor didn't betray Murkmire. Unfortunately
"ZoneID": the caves may also be home to the monstrous voriplasm

"Journal": "A mad breedsman named Drovos Nelvayn has created a dangerous new genus of kwama. These insects attack without provocation and resist any attempts at domestication. If the creatures escape
"InternalName": native kwama and the miners that tend them will suffer."
a New Life Herald in Eastmarch

"Journal": "According to a Khajiiti farmer named Halinjirr
"InternalName": a flock of bandits claimed the cavern of Zainsipilu and seized his stock of valuable crops."

"Journal": "Elfbetta
"InternalName": personal assistant to the famed explorer Narsis Dren
"Zone": informed me that the adventurer is investigating the ancestral tombs that dot the Vvardenfell landscape. They apparently uncovered an old scroll that hints at hidden treasure."

"Journal": "Another crisis looms in the Gnisis Egg Mine. Kwama workers
"InternalName": driven mad by the tonal magicks of the Dwarven resonator
"Zone": killed their queen. Without the queen
"ZoneID": the colony dies. If I do not act
column8: the mining town of Gnisis will die along with it."

"Journal": "Jee-Lar asked me to help recruit adventurers to join Cyrodilic Collections' expedition to Murkmire. Posting recruitment handbills and performing a traditional Argonian dance will help drum up interest."
"The scholar
"Zone": has a problem. One of his less savory competitors
column9: and seeks to use it to find an ancient artifact. I must stop Lenarmen before he discovers the secret of Nchulefthingth."

"Journal": "A House Redoran Councilor seeks information regarding his missing daughter
"InternalName": Veya Releth. After exhausting House resources
"Zone": he's turned to outside help in a concerted effort to find her."

"Journal": "I encountered an escaped captive named Filand who warned me that the Reachmen are kidnapping people to labor at a strange
"InternalName": ancient Forge in this valley. He asked me to help rescue the other prisoners before the Reachmen work them to death

"Journal": "Strange contraptions have emerged from a rift in the caverns beneath Tel Fyr and killed most of the Telvanni who were growing the tower. The renowned mage Divayth Fyr has asked me to accompany him in investigating this threat."
"Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a bonus for any Covenant soldier who slays 40 enemy combatants."
"With my help
"InternalName": Sun-in-Shadow achieved the rank of retainer in the Great House Telvanni. If she is to help free Eoki
"Zone": she will need to climb the ranks even further. Unfortunately
"ZoneID": becoming an oathman may present a greater challenge than she expects."

"Journal": "An elderly Dark Elf named <<1>> contracted me to transport a memory stone to locations across Vvardenfell. He wishes to archive his memories for future generations."
"Archcanon Tarvus revealed himself to be Barbas
"InternalName": the hound of Clavicus Vile. In an effort to locate and take control of Clockwork City
"Zone": he tricked me into helping him drain Lord Vivec's energy. I need to stop Barbas and recover Lord Vivec's energy."

"Journal": "Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the deadly nix-ox called Great Zexxin."
"Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the deadly nix-hound called Tarra-Suj."
"Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the giant mudcrab called Mother Jagged-Claw."
"Huntmaster Sorim-Nakar of the Erabenimsun Ashlander tribe has given me a challenge. He wants me to hunt the dire ash beetle called Ash-Eater."
"My ambitious companion
"Zone": succeeded in replacing Magister Gothren's Mouth
"ZoneID": Ralasa Delvi. But even success carries risk in Sadrith Mora. Rumor has it that Magister Gothren leaves no slight unpunished."

"Journal": "The Ashlanders of Zainab have been run out of Nchuleft
"InternalName": stopping them from scavenging the ruins for items to trade. The Temple wishes to better their relations with the tribe by gathering tools and parts which were left behind."

"Journal": "I've been hired by researchers to defeat a Hunger that's protecting a ruin they wish to study. I'm also required to gather relics scattered around the ruin."
"Even though I confirmed that Veya is safe
"InternalName": Councilor Eris continues to press me to arrange a meeting between him and his daughter."

"Journal": "Jester Queen Ayrenn has tasked me with enforcing cheer at her festivities by finding any festival goers who aren't acting the spirit of things and pelting them with flower petals."
"After a harrowing experience at the hands of Magister Gothren
"InternalName": Sun-in-Shadow finds herself at a crossroads-torn between a mage's ambition and the fruits of companionship. Dedicating herself to one may well destroy her chances at the other."

"Journal": "The miniature model of Vvardenfell is nearly complete. One section remains missing
"InternalName": which Librarian Bradyn believes is the key to finding the lost Library of Andule."

"Journal": "Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Assarnatamat and gather as many historic relics as I can find."
"Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Ashurnabitashpi and gather as many historic relics as I can find."
"Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Dushariran and gather as many historic relics as I can find."
"Numani-Rasi of the Urshilaku Ashlander tribe has requested that I explore the ruins of the Daedric shrine Ashalmawia and gather as many historic relics as I can find."
"Jester King Jorunn requested that I steal his bride-to-be away from her minders
"InternalName": so she may join him in his Feast of Fools."

"Journal": "With the revelation that Veya's brother is dead
"InternalName": Councilor Eris has asked me to keep his daughter away from Balmora and House Redoran while he looks into what happened. In the meantime
"Zone": Ashur asked me to talk to Veya."

"Journal": "I have been asked to retrieve taxes and records stolen by bandits."
"An oracle of Azura named Rhea Opacarius needs my help. Some malevolent force conspires to destroy her order and
"A local crafter
"Zone": hopes to establish a trade agreement with Captain Jimila to sell an Argonian musical instrument abroad. He wants me to act as his agent and secure a deal for his vossa-satl."

"Journal": "Veya thinks we should go and find Vatola Telem's squad that's scouting the old fort outside of Balmora. She said the fort's overrun with cultists and we need to reach the soldiers before anything happens to them."
"I found a pamphlet describing the Battlegrounds
"InternalName": a place where contests of strategy and skill are held daily."

"Journal": "Librarian Bradyn seeks the location of the lost Library of Andule
"InternalName": the secret repository of knowledge of the ancient Great Houses
"Zone": by building a miniature reproduction of Vvardenfell."

"Journal": "Battlemaster Rivyn has challenged me to participate in five Battlegrounds matches."
"Battlemaster Rivyn has challenged me to show my individual skill as a player by earning Battleground Medals."
"The Sunken Vaults of Ashalmawia are infested with Worm Cultists performing unclean rites to summon Daedra."
"The Camonna Tong are thought to be active in the illegal slave trade at Khartag Point. Their efforts need to be disrupted."
"The Divine Prosecution has requested I travel to Eton Nir Grotto and destroy the cocoons of the Daedra roaming the cavern. I'll also need to burn any sacrilegious text I find."
"A faction of bandits in a cavern called Zainsipilu are attempting to grow moon-sugar grass. I've been asked to re-direct their methods through misinformation."
"Through unknown breeding and feeding practices
"InternalName": the kwama miners of Matus-Akin have been developing a new
"Zone": more aggressive breed of kwama. Though this breed needs to be contained
"ZoneID": the Temple also wishes to learn more about their breeding methods."

"Journal": "Loremaster Celarus
"Zone": invited me to join the Psijic Order. My first task involves closing breaches in time on Summerset Isle."

"Journal": "<<1>> is willing to give me some property if I help resolve a personal matter."
"Lord Vivec wants to reward those who helped restore his power and save Vvardenfell from Barbas and Clavicus Vile. He asked me to help him accomplish that."

"Zone": was late delivering a shipment of rare mushrooms to the Telvanni mage Divayth Fyr. Though she now has the mushrooms
"ZoneID": she fears Fyr may still punish her for delivering them late."

"Journal": "Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Wardens."
"Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Wardens."
"I've run into a group of priests sermonizing about a holiday in Cyrodiil."
"A junior member of the Mages Guild named Skaldir insists that he and his associates have made a significant magical discovery-one that could prove disastrous if left uninvestigated."
"In the wake of the Shadow of Sotha Sil's attack
"InternalName": Gascone has gone missing.  I should find him and see if he has any insight into what the shadow is and why it was in the Brass Fortress."

"Journal": "<<1>> requested I gather oil from the water within Clockwork City. I'll also need to gather supplies to create more tools for future collecting."
"<<1>> requested I gather a strange material called flash stone which can be turned into a useful powder. I'll also need to collect metal pellets that help in the grinding process."
"<<1>> requested I gather the metal strands weaved within cloths in Clockwork City. I also need to collect components for an artificial lodestone that is used in harvesting the metal strands."
"<<1>> requested I gather gather the husks of Clockwork trees for an adhesive. I'll also need to collect artificial coal to help keep the sap warm."
"The Shadow of Sotha Sil
"InternalName": having claimed the Skeleton Key from the Blackfeather Court
"Zone": is making his way to the center of the Clockwork City-The Cogitum Centralis. Proctor Luciana and I must find some way to follow him."

"Journal": "One of Sotha Sil's Clockwork Apostles
"Zone": asked me to use an unusual device called a perception tabulator to find his associate and investigate a mysterious portal that appeared in the Radius."

"Journal": "According to Gascone
"InternalName": a murder of crows stole a mysterious key from his office in the Clockwork Basilica-the same key that Clavicus Vile and the mysterious shadow cultists seek. I must find this key before the enemy does."

"Journal": "<<1>> of the Undaunted has challenged me to defend the besieged city of Falkreath Hold."
"<<1>> of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Depths of Malatar.\n\nYou can only complete the Gold Key Challenge in Veteran Mode."
"The High Elf explorer
column8: have a plan to win the sponsorship of an influential Clockwork Apostle named Varuni Arvel. We'll need her support to become bonafide citizens of the Clockwork City."

"Journal": "The Halls of Regulation have begun to break down
"InternalName": threatening the water supply throughout Clockwork City. I've agreed to help <<1>> make repairs by protecting her as we gather parts and fix machinery."

"Journal": "Brengolin
"Zone": needs some assistance in creating some unconventional cuisine and I have agreed to lend him a hand."

"Journal": "Brengolin
"Zone": needs some assistance in creating some unconventional cuisine. His meat stores are presently empty
"ZoneID": so I agreed to assist him with restocking."

"Journal": "Divayth Fyr is convinced that something sinister is driving Sotha Sil's recent change of character. He asked me to help him root out the cause of the Clockwork God's new and peculiar behavior."
"<<1>> has requested my aid in helping him journey through a disease infested temple
"InternalName": located within the hazards of Scalecaller Peak."

"Journal": "Associate Zanon has asked for my assistance in rebuilding an ancient factotum. Doing so will allow him to better understand the creation of factotums
"InternalName": a mystery to all but Sotha Sil."

"Journal": "Cyrodilic Collections needs someone to collect old remains from the Teeth of Sithis for study."
"The Clockwork Apostles have sent explorers into the Shadow Cleft to find out more about the mysterious realm and the reason it's connected to Clockwork City. One explorer hasn't returned
"InternalName": and I agreed to try to find him."

"Journal": "Now that I found all of the Precursor's parts
"InternalName": Associate Zanon wishes to present the factotum to his mentor."

"Journal": "I've accepted a contract to defeat Sotha Sil's creation
"Zone": in order to test its capabilities. I've also been asked to gather its lost sequence plaques."

"Journal": "After an argument with his sister Kireth concerning Raynor's behavior during the Shadow Crisis
"InternalName": the young artificer stormed off and vowed to finish exploring the Clockwork City on his own. Kireth asked me to go help him."

"Journal": "The Clockwork Apostles sent a member of the Mages Guild through the portal to explore the Shadow Cleft. She hasn't returned."
"A Clockwork Apostle entered the Shadow Cleft and hasn't returned. What's worse
"InternalName": he forgot to take his perception tabulator with him."

"Journal": "The Clockwork Apostles have tasked me to continue maintenance in the Halls of Regulation. I need to grease a ventilation fan using oil found within the repair factotums."
"The Divine Prosecution has tasked me with taking coral crab eggs from the reef between Lillandril and the Corgrad Wastes for the Sapiarchs to inspect for signs of corruption."
"<<1>> tasked me with killing Caanerin
"Zone": and restraining her spirit by activating warding stones scattered around her ancestral glade."

"Journal": "The Divine Prosecution has charged me with clearing out Welenkin Cove and eliminating the threat posed by B'Korgen
"The Office of Divine Prosecution suffered a number of casualties to a creature called Graveld in Sil-Var-Woad."
"The Clockwork Apostles have tasked me to continue maintenance in the Halls of Regulation. I need to replace several water filters in order to stop the possibility of contamination."
"Three Dark Elf Saints were granted the gift of immortality
"InternalName": in the form of ageless mechanical bodies created by the god Sotha Sil
"Zone": at the price of their sanity. Now their madness poses a significant threat to the Clockwork City."

"Journal": "I found an inactive brassilisk in the Radius of the Clockwork City with the name \"Frynga\" carved into its jaw. If I find Frynga and return her mechanical pet
"I found a sequence plaque on the road in the Clockwork City Radius. An engraving on the plaque asks that it be returned to the Clockwork Registrar in the Brass Fortress."
"I received an enchanted stone from the Mages Guild that contains an important message from Vanus Galerion."
"I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver alchemical products to an interested organization."

"Journal": "The Bursar of Tribute demands compensation for the Blackfeather Court from mortals who refuse to allow them to play with their games and toys."
"The Ritemaster used scrying magic to recall some of his missing memories. He took the Heart of Transparent Law into the Dreaming Cave beneath Ceporah Tower
"InternalName": but he still can't remember what happened after that. I need to help him remember."

"Journal": "The Bursar of Tributes seeks ornate items to add to the Blackfeather Court's hoard."
"Ritemaster Iachesis of the Psijic Order plans to use an augury ritual to reveal the secrets of the strange pearl we recovered from the Monastery of Serene Harmony."
"Ritemaster Iachesis remembers a woman's voice
"InternalName": whispering ancient words over and over. He thinks these words are tied to the place where he hid the Heart of Transparent Law. Before we breach the barrier
"Zone": we need to determine what the words mean."

"Journal": "Rinyde has asked me to find her brother Larydel and stop him from joining the House of Reveries. I must audition as well in order to figure out who he is."
"Students in the Illumination Academy have taken on bizarre personae and don't appear to know who or where they are. I must help them reclaim their lost identities."
"A distraught mother named Lanarie cannot find her son
"InternalName": Arathel. The youth surrendered to the authorities-saying he was part of a plot to kill a Sapiarch. But he disappeared from his cell shortly thereafter. I promised Lanarie I would find her son."

"Journal": "I met a High Elf bailiff outside the ruins of the Direnni Acropolis. He told me that an ancient curse lingers within its walls. I must find the source of this corruption and cleanse it."
"I agreed to escort the scholar Andewen as she investigates an ancient temple
"InternalName": hidden within the mysterious forest of Ebon Stadmont."

"Journal": "I met a keeper of the Royal Menagerie in Sil-Var-Woad. He warned me that dangerous animals have escaped into the park grounds
"InternalName": but he is searching for a tame indrik that may have escaped during the chaos."

"Journal": "I negotiated an alliance of sorts with Clavicus Vile and Mephala. They agreed to help us get into the Crystal Tower-mostly. Once inside
"InternalName": I need to find a way to stop Nocturnal before she uses the tower to remake reality."

"Journal": "Ulliceta
"InternalName": an apprentice studying under the Psijics
"Zone": took a powerful seeing stone called the Eye of Remembrance to the forbidden Traitor's Vault. It may reveal the secrets hidden there."

"Journal": "Tindoria
"Zone": has hired me to acquire a list of rare art supplies for her next masterpiece."

"Journal": "Felande Demarie
"Zone": is looking for a tenant of good reputation to give her inn room to."

"Journal": "A massive storm is brewing over the fortress of Sea Keep that is the work of a Maormer Sea Mage. It will devastate the entire coast unless the Sea Mage's spell is stopped."
"A prominent High Elf named Halimorion was murdered by a folkloric assassin called the Ghost of the Green. But there may be more to this case than meets the eye."
"Seeks-the-Dark was hired to steal tokens from a cult within Eton Nir Grotto. Unexpectedly
"InternalName": the cult has been massacred by Daedra who now lurk within. I've been hired to collect the tokens and find Seek-the-Dark's assistant

"Journal": "Tableau is an artist fascinated by the outcasts known as hulkynd
"InternalName": and wishes to meet one. She's requested I help arrange a meeting with one who was seen outside of Rellenthil."

"Journal": "Tableau is debuting as an artist. Manacar fears that she may be in danger. He's asked me to help things run smoothly."
"The Sea Sload altered the Ritemaster's memories and forced him to steal the Heart of Transparent Law and hide it away. While he works to unlock his memories
"InternalName": he wants Valsirenn and I to warn the keepers of the Crystal Tower

"Journal": "Esterdel asked me to find <<1>>
"InternalName": his missing bride-to-be. He tracked her to Archon's Grove
"Zone": which has been overrun by werewolves. He's hired me to rescue Niralin
"ZoneID": or at least collect proof that she's died."

"Journal": "A group of outcasts living in the seclusion of the Corgrad Wastes has seen their number dwindle after a string of disappearances. They believe the source of the trouble lies in the old buried ruins exposed by the recent sinkholes plaguing the region."
"An Altmer woman approached me with questions about her father
"InternalName": Curtaros. His angler fleet is long overdue from their voyage to Wasten Coraldale and she's concerned for his safety. I have agreed to locate her father for her."

"Journal": "<<1>> wants me to recover articles of faith on behalf of the cult of Phynaster."
"With the Crystal Tower saved
"InternalName": Valsirenn wishes to call a meeting of Summerset's most influential leaders to ensure its future protection."

"Journal": "Battlereeve Tanerline charged me with finding allies to attack the abyssal geysers and destroy the pearls that power them before the Sea Sload cabal's plan to sink Summerset comes to fruition."
"I received a voucher for a special-occasion cake from the renowned master baker
"A number of adventurers have fallen prey to the magic of a mind trap. A mage named Oriandra has a plan to rescue them
"InternalName": but she needs my help to succeed."

"Journal": "I found the corpse of Nafarion
"InternalName": a High Elf who turned into a vampire. His dying wish was for his betrothed to know the truth about what happened to him."

"Journal": "A High Elf named Vinafwe is being plagued by a vandal who is ruining her carefully arranged botanical grounds with foreign flowers and even dangerous stranglers."
"Miranrel and her companions were attacked by gryphons after entering their nesting grounds. She's offered me a reward if I help find her lost friends."
"I encountered a noblewoman along the beach who has lost her husband and her prized hound. I have agreed to help reunite them with her."
"Loremaster Celarus's apprentice
"Zone": charged me with sealing more time breaches for the Psijic Order-this time in the Iliac Bay region."

"Journal": "A new cluster of time breaches appeared in northeastern Tamriel-specifically the lands of Stonefalls. Eastmarch
"InternalName": and The Rift. As an agent of the Psijic Order

"Journal": "The Ashlander Hanu has recruited me to join her hunting team within Hircine's Hunting Grounds. We must hunt down an indrik and present its heart to Hircine in order for Hanu to win a boon from the Daedric Prince and save her father."
"Even with all eight fragments of the Staff of Towers collected
"InternalName": time breaches continue to open all across Tamriel. I must seal a new cluster of these rifts in the land of Rivenspire."

"Journal": "Loremaster Celarus feels confident that the threat posed by the Staff of Towers is nearly dealt with. Unfortunately
"InternalName": there is one final cluster of time breaches in the land of Craglorn. I need to seal them."

"Journal": "Loremaster Celarus's apprentice
"Zone": stole the eight fragments of the Staff of Towers and fled to Tamriel. She no doubt plans to reforge the staff and use it to alter time. The results could be catastrophic. I must stop her before it's too late."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Fort Glademist
"Zone": and Fort Warden for the Pact."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture Castle Faregyl
"Zone": and Castle Bloodmayne for the Pact."

"Journal": "I accepted a mission to help capture any three keeps for the Dominion."
"I accepted a mission to help capture any three keeps for the Covenant."
"I accepted a mission to help capture the towns of Vlastarus
"I accepted a mission to help reclaim Fort Glademist
"Zone": and Fort Warden for the Covenant."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Jewelry to an interested organization."

"Journal": "I've taken a contract from one of the Writ boards
"InternalName": an agreement to deliver Jewelry to an interested organization."

"Journal": "Bolu of the Dead-Water tribe
"Zone": wants me to go to the Echoing Hollow and accomplish the task he set before me."

"Journal": "After a lengthy chase and a harrowing battle with Kassandra
"InternalName": Famia and I finally retrieved the Remnant of Argon. Now
"Zone": we need to learn how to release the souls that reside within it."

"Journal": "Cyrodilic Collections seeks scriptures relating to ancient Argonian worship of Sithis."
"I encountered an expedition party searching for a Dwarven vault in a glacier. Their leader
"Zone": made me an offer to assist her in locating an artifact known as the Wrathstone."

"Journal": "Varo Hosidias of Cyrodilic Collections wants me to enter the Tsofeer Cavern and place sacred Argonian candles at the behest of a benefactor named Tia Doran."
"My companion from the xanmeer
"Zone": needs my help. Several of her employees have gone missing in recent days
"ZoneID": and she fears the worst. I need to try to find out what happened to them."

"Journal": "Erilthel has requested that I help save her boss Seeks-the-Dark by completing a gauntlet held by the Blackguards. I'll have to make my way through the many foes of Blackrose Prison and emerge victorious."
"Twelve tablets were stolen from the Xinchei-Konu
"InternalName": an ancient Argonian calendar. Jekka-Wass Vozei
"ZoneID": has tasked me to return the first missing tablet."

"Journal": "<<1>> asked if I could head into the swamp and look for her missing wife
"Hands-That-Heal has lost a wooden box with great sentimental value to him after being attacked by hackwings. He's offered a reward if I successfully return the box to him."
"Several envoys from the Root-Whisper Village have gone missing
"InternalName": and Tuwul suspects that Blackguards are the ones responsible."

"Journal": "Several offerings collected by the Root-Whisper Tribe have been stolen by the Blackguards. If these offerings aren't recovered
"InternalName": the other tribes will become deeply offended."

"Journal": "Zahari asked me to help train new recruits for the Khajiit Defense Legion to fight enemies they may not have encountered in training."
"Dragons have not been seen in Tamriel for generations
"InternalName": and the Khajiit are unsure how best to fight against them. The ancient Nords recorded Dragon fighting techniques on scrolls they keep in their crypts. I need to find these scrolls."
